WEBVTT

1
00:01:16.355 --> 00:01:18.519
Best place we went to
since we've been here.

2
00:01:18.620 --> 00:01:19.896
Definitely. man.

3
00:01:19.996 --> 00:01:21.689
- Way to go. buddy.
- Brother.

4
00:01:21.789 --> 00:01:25.384
- You guys coming back to my place?
- All right. Let's go.

5
00:01:28.588 --> 00:01:30.013
Hey!

6
00:01:30.549 --> 00:01:34.143
Shame. shame.
Closing down the beer garden.

7
00:01:34.343 --> 00:01:37.896
Hundred-meter dash powered
by knackwurst and lager.

8
00:01:38.890 --> 00:01:41.108
Where are you guys from?

9
00:01:42.186 --> 00:01:44.152
What's your event?

10
00:01:45.855 --> 00:01:47.990
They don't speak English. man.

11
00:01:49.526 --> 00:01:53.097
- Let's help them over.
- Come on. Up?

12
00:01:53.197 --> 00:01:54.746
Here you go.

13
00:01:55.615 --> 00:01:58.209
Let's go. I got you. Come on.

14
00:01:59.912 --> 00:02:03.004
Up. Yeah. All right?

15
00:02:07.920 --> 00:02:10.346
- You guys take care.
- See you.

16
00:02:12.049 --> 00:02:13.825
- Take it easy.
- See you.

17
00:02:13.925 --> 00:02:15.828
You're taking the grade tomorrow.

18
00:02:15.927 --> 00:02:17.937
Watch yourself. man.

19
00:03:05.352 --> 00:03:07.735
(SPEAKING ARABIC)

20
00:03:20.700 --> 00:03:22.334
(DOORKNOB JANGLING)

21
00:03:35.507 --> 00:03:37.557
(YELLING IN ARABIC)

22
00:03:42.639 --> 00:03:44.147
(YELLING IN HEBREW AND ARABIC)

23
00:03:53.650 --> 00:03:55.009
I'm Jim McKay speaking to you live...

24
00:03:55.110 --> 00:03:57.554
at this moment. from ABC headquarters...

25
00:03:57.653 --> 00:04:00.848
just outside the Olympic village
in Munich. West Germany.

26
00:04:00.949 --> 00:04:03.894
The peace of what have been
called the "serene Olympics"...

27
00:04:03.993 --> 00:04:07.837
was shattered just before dawn
this morning. about 5:00.

28
00:04:08.581 --> 00:04:11.193
REPORTER: (ON TV) There is great
uncertainty about how many Israelis...

29
00:04:11.293 --> 00:04:13.528
are being held hostage in the apartment.

30
00:04:13.628 --> 00:04:16.406
It now appears that Black September
has tossed a piece of paper...

31
00:04:16.505 --> 00:04:18.783
out the window. A list of demands.

32
00:04:18.884 --> 00:04:21.452
They want what they call
"the Israeli war machine"...

33
00:04:21.552 --> 00:04:25.374
to release 200 Arabs.
which it insists are political prisoners...

34
00:04:25.473 --> 00:04:28.024
or the hostages will be killed.

35
00:04:28.143 --> 00:04:30.086
The terrorist communiqué
ends with an appeal...

36
00:04:30.187 --> 00:04:33.613
for revolutionaries
of the world to unite.

37
00:04:33.981 --> 00:04:37.742
McKAY: (ON TV) This is building
number 31. At this moment...

38
00:04:38.194 --> 00:04:41.305
eight or nine terrified
living human beings...

39
00:04:41.406 --> 00:04:43.266
are being held prisoner.

40
00:04:43.367 --> 00:04:47.103
The demands have been many...
There's someone right now.

41
00:04:47.204 --> 00:04:49.480
This certainly has to be
one of the guerrillas.

42
00:04:49.581 --> 00:04:53.151
A man with a stocking mask
on his face. Weird.

43
00:04:53.250 --> 00:04:55.987
What's going on inside
that head and that mind?

44
00:04:56.088 --> 00:04:57.947
JENNINGS:
Just a short while ago. there was...

45
00:04:58.048 --> 00:05:00.951
another in this long series
of negotiations.

46
00:05:01.050 --> 00:05:05.581
The spokesman for the group
came out. spoke. went back.

47
00:05:05.680 --> 00:05:09.334
It seems to be a process
of speak and consultation.

48
00:05:09.434 --> 00:05:12.295
McKAY: Does it mean it's all right?
Or does it mean it's all over?

49
00:05:12.396 --> 00:05:13.838
Come and get us.

50
00:05:13.939 --> 00:05:16.591
As Peter Jennings indicated.
the German army...

51
00:05:16.692 --> 00:05:20.220
because of very complicated laws...

52
00:05:20.319 --> 00:05:22.014
would not be allowed to participate.

53
00:05:22.113 --> 00:05:25.309
And there you see an athlete
holding a canvas bag...

54
00:05:25.408 --> 00:05:27.394
in which is obviously a machine gun.

55
00:05:27.494 --> 00:05:29.312
Peter Jennings.
once again. is stationed...

56
00:05:29.413 --> 00:05:31.648
inside the Olympic village.
With the naked eye. Peter...

57
00:05:31.747 --> 00:05:33.149
what do you see now?

58
00:05:33.250 --> 00:05:36.110
Jim. there are now a great many...

59
00:05:36.211 --> 00:05:39.697
maybe a dozen already.
of those security men...

60
00:05:39.798 --> 00:05:42.348
in athletic uniforms.

61
00:05:43.175 --> 00:05:44.976
(SPEAKING ARABIC)

62
00:06:02.446 --> 00:06:03.829
Stop!

63
00:06:04.572 --> 00:06:07.016
REPORTER: (ON TV) It now appears that
the siege of the apartment building...

64
00:06:07.117 --> 00:06:09.185
where the hostages are being
held has been called off...

65
00:06:09.286 --> 00:06:11.187
and the German police are
retreating from the area.

66
00:06:11.288 --> 00:06:13.273
Officials seem to have decided
to abandon their plans...

67
00:06:13.372 --> 00:06:15.524
when the leader of the fedayeen
came out of the building...

68
00:06:15.625 --> 00:06:18.778
and demanded they call off the siege
pointing out that the entire operation...

69
00:06:18.879 --> 00:06:21.156
was being watched on a television set
within the apartment.

70
00:06:21.255 --> 00:06:23.533
Apparently. new demands have
been made to move the fedayeen...

71
00:06:23.632 --> 00:06:25.701
and their hostages.
though it isn't yet known...

72
00:06:25.802 --> 00:06:27.329
when or where this might occur.

73
00:06:27.428 --> 00:06:31.290
This is Peter. Do you have something
to report to us from where you are?

74
00:06:31.391 --> 00:06:33.961
This is Cosell. I certainly do. Peter.

75
00:06:34.060 --> 00:06:37.088
We have an immense
flurry of action here.

76
00:06:37.189 --> 00:06:41.843
Suddenly. in the whole area between
building 20 and building 12...

77
00:06:41.942 --> 00:06:43.971
they have been clearing out cars.

78
00:06:44.071 --> 00:06:47.098
Obviously wary of an assault
from the German police...

79
00:06:47.199 --> 00:06:50.334
(REPORTERS SPEAKING
IN DIFFERENT LANGUAGES)

80
00:07:01.295 --> 00:07:02.697
COSELL: within five minutes.

81
00:07:02.798 --> 00:07:04.365
REPORTER:
What I'm hearing from here is that...

82
00:07:04.466 --> 00:07:08.161
they're heading to an airport
called Fürstenfeldbruck.

83
00:07:08.261 --> 00:07:09.704
REPORTER:
...says the chopper just landed...

84
00:07:09.805 --> 00:07:11.081
at the back of the Olympic village here.

85
00:07:11.180 --> 00:07:12.915
Can you see gate number seven?

86
00:07:13.016 --> 00:07:15.752
This is Vance Kolvig.
What I have seen are...

87
00:07:15.851 --> 00:07:18.588
four hostages in one helicopter...

88
00:07:18.687 --> 00:07:21.966
and it looks like five hostages
in the first helicopter.

89
00:07:22.067 --> 00:07:23.927
Yes. I just got back
a little while ago...

90
00:07:24.026 --> 00:07:26.096
and it was obvious that something...

91
00:07:26.196 --> 00:07:27.514
quite serious was going on out there.

92
00:07:27.613 --> 00:07:30.016
REPORTER: Here we are. outside the gates.
There are armored cars...

93
00:07:30.117 --> 00:07:31.100
police cars...

94
00:07:31.201 --> 00:07:32.269
(SPEAKING ARABIC)

95
00:07:32.369 --> 00:07:34.646
Police are pouring in through
the gates with lights flashing...

96
00:07:34.745 --> 00:07:36.981
and here come some more.
Five. six. here comes another one.

97
00:07:37.081 --> 00:07:39.401
Seven armored cars have gone
in through the gates now.

98
00:07:39.500 --> 00:07:41.153
They're mounting a major invasion.

99
00:07:41.252 --> 00:07:43.572
The latest word we get
from the airport is that...

100
00:07:43.672 --> 00:07:46.180
quote. "all hell has
broken loose out there."

101
00:07:46.882 --> 00:07:49.143
(SPEAKING GERMAN)

102
00:07:57.226 --> 00:07:58.651
(EXPLOSION)

103
00:08:02.399 --> 00:08:04.300
It's just arrived. Peter.
The bus has arrived...

104
00:08:04.401 --> 00:08:06.470
- to the helicopters.
- We have reports now...

105
00:08:06.569 --> 00:08:10.538
that all the hostages.
all nine hostages are safe.

106
00:08:10.656 --> 00:08:14.644
We repeat. we have confirmed.
it's just past 1:00 a.m.

107
00:08:14.744 --> 00:08:16.437
The fighting ceased at midnight.

108
00:08:16.538 --> 00:08:18.564
Well. that's at least 24
we've seen go in...

109
00:08:18.665 --> 00:08:20.149
and now we can see
the lights flashing...

110
00:08:20.250 --> 00:08:22.860
There was a terrible battle at
the airport. but the hostages...

111
00:08:22.961 --> 00:08:25.488
somehow the hostages are safe.

112
00:08:25.588 --> 00:08:28.074
And. according to these reports.
all Arab terrorists...

113
00:08:28.175 --> 00:08:29.867
have died by German gunfire.

114
00:08:29.968 --> 00:08:32.995
Originally it was said that
the hostages were safe...

115
00:08:33.096 --> 00:08:35.164
but now that has been changed.

116
00:08:35.264 --> 00:08:37.417
An Olympic spokesman said that...

117
00:08:37.517 --> 00:08:39.503
CIOFFI: Of the areas in the world.
this is one of the areas...

118
00:08:39.602 --> 00:08:40.943
(SPEAKING HEBREW)

119
00:08:45.442 --> 00:08:47.344
They've spent their youth.
their young people...

120
00:08:47.443 --> 00:08:48.845
they've spent all their money on wars.

121
00:08:48.945 --> 00:08:51.639
Now they have a chance to build
their nations. These nations...

122
00:08:51.740 --> 00:08:54.308
And. of course. they're compatible.
The Arabs and the Israelis...

123
00:08:54.408 --> 00:08:56.186
are perfectly compatible
as far as I can tell.

124
00:08:56.286 --> 00:08:58.105
And now. as you say.
Peter. you're quite right.

125
00:08:58.205 --> 00:09:00.398
They've been jolted apart again.
as they were...

126
00:09:00.498 --> 00:09:03.360
seeming to come just a little closer.
Little hope.

127
00:09:03.460 --> 00:09:05.861
We've just gotten the final word.
When I was a kid...

128
00:09:05.961 --> 00:09:08.532
my father used to say our greatest
hopes and our worst fears...

129
00:09:08.631 --> 00:09:12.119
are seldom realized. Our worst
fears have been realized tonight.

130
00:09:12.219 --> 00:09:15.038
They've now said that
there were 11 hostages.

131
00:09:15.138 --> 00:09:17.940
Two were killed in their rooms...

132
00:09:18.557 --> 00:09:20.376
yesterday morning.

133
00:09:20.476 --> 00:09:24.880
Nine were killed at the airport tonight.

134
00:09:24.980 --> 00:09:26.865
They're all gone.

135
00:09:27.234 --> 00:09:29.885
REPORTER:
...before a quiet crowd of 80.000.

136
00:09:29.985 --> 00:09:32.096
After the ceremony.
the surviving team...

137
00:09:32.197 --> 00:09:34.182
saw the coffins of their
fallen comrades...

138
00:09:34.282 --> 00:09:37.018
loaded onto an airplane to
bring them home together.

139
00:09:37.118 --> 00:09:39.687
Enormous crowds also gathered
on Dizengoff Street...

140
00:09:39.788 --> 00:09:43.232
and in Jerusalem on the plaza
in front of the Knesset.

141
00:09:43.332 --> 00:09:45.943
People are weeping.
tearing their clothes.

142
00:09:46.043 --> 00:09:48.738
The funerals. which will be
held tomorrow in Jerusalem...

143
00:09:48.837 --> 00:09:51.700
are expected to draw tens
of thousands of mourners.

144
00:09:51.799 --> 00:09:54.244
These are the names of the
members of the Israeli team...

145
00:09:54.344 --> 00:09:56.620
at the Munich Olympics.
who were held hostage...

146
00:09:56.721 --> 00:10:00.315
beaten. and finally murdered
by Arab terrorists.

147
00:10:00.475 --> 00:10:02.442
Yosef Gottfreund.

148
00:10:02.686 --> 00:10:04.587
Eliezaar Halfen.

149
00:10:04.687 --> 00:10:06.613
Yakov Springer.

150
00:10:07.649 --> 00:10:09.740
Dr. Wadi Haddad.

151
00:10:10.150 --> 00:10:11.743
Abu Daoud.

152
00:10:11.986 --> 00:10:13.263
Mahmoud Hamshari.

153
00:10:13.363 --> 00:10:15.205
Andre Spitzer.

154
00:10:15.532 --> 00:10:17.374
Zeev Friedman.

155
00:10:17.575 --> 00:10:18.851
Kehat Schur.

156
00:10:18.951 --> 00:10:20.711
Wael Zwaiter.

157
00:10:20.953 --> 00:10:23.087
Dr. Basil al-Kubaisi.

158
00:10:23.373 --> 00:10:24.566
Kamal Nasser.

159
00:10:24.666 --> 00:10:26.508
Mark Slavin.

160
00:10:26.668 --> 00:10:28.552
Amitzur Shapira.

161
00:10:28.919 --> 00:10:30.678
David Berger.

162
00:10:30.838 --> 00:10:32.556
Kemal Adwan.

163
00:10:33.173 --> 00:10:34.850
Abu Youssef.

164
00:10:34.967 --> 00:10:35.951
Mohammed Boudia.

165
00:10:36.052 --> 00:10:37.703
Yosef Romano.

166
00:10:37.803 --> 00:10:39.479
Moshe Weinberg.

167
00:10:39.722 --> 00:10:41.249
Hussein al-Chir.

168
00:10:41.349 --> 00:10:43.274
Ali Hassan Salameh.

169
00:10:46.812 --> 00:10:49.883
(ON TV) As all of Israel mourns.
of course everyone says prayers...

170
00:10:49.982 --> 00:10:50.966
for the people...

171
00:10:51.067 --> 00:10:53.886
I tried not to think about you.
but I couldn't.

172
00:10:53.986 --> 00:10:57.974
...a very private. terrible grief
in the days and years to come.

173
00:10:58.073 --> 00:11:02.394
I have the world's most boring job.
What's going to happen to me?

174
00:11:02.495 --> 00:11:05.023
Well. they were just athletes.
They went to the Olympics.

175
00:11:05.123 --> 00:11:07.381
Look what happened to them.

176
00:11:09.793 --> 00:11:11.385
What now?

177
00:11:13.673 --> 00:11:16.224
Now we're going to have a baby.

178
00:11:18.635 --> 00:11:20.394
Eleven names.

179
00:11:20.638 --> 00:11:24.066
Give us the order. and we'll begin.

180
00:11:27.604 --> 00:11:29.863
It's the same as Eichmann.

181
00:11:30.815 --> 00:11:32.341
We say to these butchers:

182
00:11:32.442 --> 00:11:34.260
"You didn't want to share
this world with us...

183
00:11:34.360 --> 00:11:37.078
"then we don't have to
share this world with you."

184
00:11:38.447 --> 00:11:41.540
There's legitimacy for this.
Am I correct?

185
00:11:44.537 --> 00:11:47.172
Ambushed and slaughtered again...

186
00:11:48.832 --> 00:11:52.278
while the rest of the world is
playing games. Olympic torches...

187
00:11:52.379 --> 00:11:55.471
and brass bands
and dead Jews in Germany.

188
00:11:55.798 --> 00:11:57.866
And the world couldn't care less.

189
00:11:57.966 --> 00:12:00.035
We've responded.
We sent 70 fighter jets.

190
00:12:00.135 --> 00:12:01.288
A response no one heard.

191
00:12:01.388 --> 00:12:03.914
Air strikes on guerrilla training centers.
That's a response.

192
00:12:04.014 --> 00:12:05.917
No one notices what happens
in the border camps.

193
00:12:06.017 --> 00:12:08.711
Sixty Arabs dead. at least.
Who knows how many wounded.

194
00:12:08.812 --> 00:12:11.214
This is about fixing
the world's attention.

195
00:12:11.313 --> 00:12:13.966
Well. it's not just a publicity stunt.

196
00:12:14.067 --> 00:12:15.991
Let me remind you.

197
00:12:16.152 --> 00:12:20.307
Ali Hassan Salameh.
he invented Black September.

198
00:12:20.407 --> 00:12:23.457
He is the architect
of the Munich murders.

199
00:12:24.369 --> 00:12:26.211
These people.

200
00:12:26.745 --> 00:12:29.172
They're sworn to destroy us.

201
00:12:31.333 --> 00:12:33.509
Forget peace for now.

202
00:12:33.711 --> 00:12:36.471
We have to show them we're strong.

203
00:12:36.880 --> 00:12:40.100
We have laws. we represent civilization.

204
00:12:40.509 --> 00:12:43.120
Some people say we can't
afford to be civilized.

205
00:12:43.221 --> 00:12:45.855
I've always resisted such people.

206
00:12:46.807 --> 00:12:49.001
But I don't know
who these maniacs are...

207
00:12:49.101 --> 00:12:51.403
and where they come from.

208
00:12:52.355 --> 00:12:54.114
Palestinians?

209
00:12:54.274 --> 00:12:56.490
They're not recognizable.

210
00:12:59.320 --> 00:13:02.873
You tell me what law
protects people like these.

211
00:13:05.869 --> 00:13:08.461
Today I'm hearing with new ears.

212
00:13:09.746 --> 00:13:12.192
Every civilization finds it necessary...

213
00:13:12.292 --> 00:13:16.344
to negotiate compromises
with its own values.

214
00:13:18.965 --> 00:13:20.741
I've made a decision.

215
00:13:20.841 --> 00:13:23.601
The responsibility is entirely mine.

216
00:13:31.686 --> 00:13:33.379
- Avner?
- Yes?

217
00:13:33.480 --> 00:13:36.114
We're going to Jerusalem. Get in.

218
00:13:37.734 --> 00:13:39.533
Come on. sir.

219
00:13:47.701 --> 00:13:50.187
Hello. I'm General Zamir.

220
00:13:50.288 --> 00:13:51.671
Yes.

221
00:13:52.039 --> 00:13:53.649
You swore us in.

222
00:13:53.750 --> 00:13:55.943
My unit. when I joined Mossad.

223
00:13:56.043 --> 00:13:58.094
I don't remember you.

224
00:13:59.047 --> 00:14:01.514
Of course. I know your father.

225
00:14:11.267 --> 00:14:12.734
Avner.

226
00:14:14.312 --> 00:14:17.548
- It's been...
- Two years since I worked for you.

227
00:14:17.649 --> 00:14:20.491
I remember. Please. sit down.

228
00:14:21.528 --> 00:14:23.077
Harari.

229
00:14:23.613 --> 00:14:25.413
General Nadav.

230
00:14:25.822 --> 00:14:27.791
And General Yariv.

231
00:14:28.283 --> 00:14:30.519
How are you? How is your father?

232
00:14:30.620 --> 00:14:32.671
He's fine. Thank you.

233
00:14:34.374 --> 00:14:37.443
Coffee? It's wonderful to see you again.

234
00:14:37.543 --> 00:14:38.927
Sit.

235
00:14:41.713 --> 00:14:43.825
The chief of the Mossad. two generals...

236
00:14:43.924 --> 00:14:46.976
and the Prime Minister.
Obviously. it's important.

237
00:14:49.346 --> 00:14:51.290
This is something new.

238
00:14:51.390 --> 00:14:54.149
What happened in Munich
changes everything.

239
00:14:56.437 --> 00:14:59.990
We want to ask you.
Will you undertake a mission?

240
00:15:00.441 --> 00:15:03.595
An important mission.
You will have to leave the country...

241
00:15:03.695 --> 00:15:05.971
and your family. maybe for years.

242
00:15:06.072 --> 00:15:08.975
- And it is dangerous.
- You can't talk about it to anyone.

243
00:15:09.075 --> 00:15:11.000
Not even your wife.

244
00:15:15.539 --> 00:15:18.008
Now you should say something.

245
00:15:18.835 --> 00:15:21.135
Do you have any questions?

246
00:15:22.963 --> 00:15:26.600
So. this isn't about guarding
tourists on El Al jets?

247
00:15:28.970 --> 00:15:30.687
No questions?

248
00:15:30.888 --> 00:15:33.648
Did we mention how dangerous it is?

249
00:15:33.932 --> 00:15:36.650
You know. my sister died on Tuesday.

250
00:15:36.769 --> 00:15:39.254
- No. I didn't know that.
- Cancer.

251
00:15:39.355 --> 00:15:41.758
I couldn't go to
the athletes' funerals...

252
00:15:41.857 --> 00:15:43.658
because she died.

253
00:15:45.028 --> 00:15:48.078
That upset people.
but she was my sister.

254
00:15:49.323 --> 00:15:51.165
Family matters.

255
00:15:55.370 --> 00:15:58.899
- Your wife is pregnant.
- Yes. seven months.

256
00:15:59.000 --> 00:16:00.508
Mazel tov.

257
00:16:01.043 --> 00:16:03.278
You were one of my favorite bodyguards.

258
00:16:03.379 --> 00:16:06.389
You know. I like neat. durable men.

259
00:16:06.673 --> 00:16:09.725
You liked having the son
of a hero around.

260
00:16:11.220 --> 00:16:14.039
Truth be told.
you don't look much like your father.

261
00:16:14.139 --> 00:16:15.565
No?

262
00:16:17.393 --> 00:16:20.028
Your mother is who you resemble.

263
00:16:38.623 --> 00:16:40.548
Tomorrow morning.

264
00:16:40.792 --> 00:16:43.467
If you can't decide in one day...

265
00:16:44.044 --> 00:16:45.928
you can't decide.

266
00:16:55.597 --> 00:16:56.957
Her sister died.

267
00:16:57.057 --> 00:16:59.626
But I think she didn't go
to the athletes' funerals...

268
00:16:59.726 --> 00:17:01.379
because some people are angry at her...

269
00:17:01.479 --> 00:17:04.405
for not negotiating with the terrorists.

270
00:17:11.905 --> 00:17:13.348
She didn't go to the funerals...

271
00:17:13.449 --> 00:17:15.684
because she didn't want to be booed.

272
00:17:15.785 --> 00:17:18.104
It's a good sign
you didn't ask questions.

273
00:17:18.203 --> 00:17:19.564
You'll say yes.

274
00:17:19.663 --> 00:17:23.173
I'm your case officer.
My name is Ephraim.

275
00:17:24.585 --> 00:17:27.386
(PANTING)

276
00:17:48.608 --> 00:17:52.703
How late in the pregnancy before
you have to stop having sex?

277
00:17:54.781 --> 00:17:56.290
Labor.

278
00:18:10.006 --> 00:18:13.098
Don't worry about it.
You won't be around.

279
00:18:14.676 --> 00:18:16.185
Will you?

280
00:18:18.472 --> 00:18:20.958
Whatever they want.
make sure they give you a raise.

281
00:18:21.057 --> 00:18:23.377
I need things for the baby.

282
00:18:23.478 --> 00:18:25.987
I can't live with refusing this.

283
00:18:27.647 --> 00:18:30.657
Your mother.
she knew what she was doing.

284
00:18:30.984 --> 00:18:33.596
- She abandoned you on that kibbutz.
- She didn't abandon me.

285
00:18:33.695 --> 00:18:35.097
My father was missing.

286
00:18:35.198 --> 00:18:37.517
He was in prison. she was overwhelmed.

287
00:18:37.616 --> 00:18:40.478
- Oh. yes.
- She did what anybody would do.

288
00:18:40.577 --> 00:18:44.172
Yeah. so she took you to the
kibbutz and abandoned you.

289
00:18:44.749 --> 00:18:47.549
Now you think Israel is your mother.

290
00:18:54.217 --> 00:18:55.849
So listen.

291
00:18:56.719 --> 00:19:00.020
I'm going to go along with this.
until I don't.

292
00:19:01.097 --> 00:19:04.317
- Do you understand me?
- I love you.

293
00:19:07.395 --> 00:19:09.864
I'm not the hero's nice wife.

294
00:19:15.738 --> 00:19:20.165
First you resign from Mossad.
Your new contract.

295
00:19:21.035 --> 00:19:24.020
It says we do not employ you.
offer you benefits. or pensions...

296
00:19:24.121 --> 00:19:26.816
or legal aid or medical assistance.

297
00:19:26.915 --> 00:19:29.968
It's a contract that
there is no contract.

298
00:19:30.419 --> 00:19:32.320
- Do I get a copy?
- You don't.

299
00:19:32.421 --> 00:19:35.056
Your pension contribution refund.

300
00:19:35.383 --> 00:19:37.451
You're now officially unofficial.

301
00:19:37.551 --> 00:19:39.810
Unemployed and uninsured.

302
00:19:41.096 --> 00:19:42.623
You'll open two accounts...

303
00:19:42.722 --> 00:19:45.000
at the Union de
Banques Suisse in Geneva...

304
00:19:45.101 --> 00:19:46.544
on Rue du Commerce.

305
00:19:46.644 --> 00:19:50.173
Operational funds in one box.
in the other your salary...

306
00:19:50.272 --> 00:19:52.424
which you don't take
till the mission ends...

307
00:19:52.525 --> 00:19:54.176
when you get what accumulates.

308
00:19:54.277 --> 00:19:57.096
Also. for each of your men.
you open an account for his salary.

309
00:19:57.195 --> 00:20:01.183
- How many men do I have for this...
- In the operational funds box...

310
00:20:01.284 --> 00:20:05.377
we will deposit 250.000
American dollars.

311
00:20:05.621 --> 00:20:08.398
You take it out. we put more in.

312
00:20:08.499 --> 00:20:10.902
I want receipts.

313
00:20:11.001 --> 00:20:12.987
You are not working for
the Baron Rothschild.

314
00:20:13.086 --> 00:20:15.364
You're working for Israel.
a small country.

315
00:20:15.463 --> 00:20:18.951
I'm an old Galicianer from
a mud hut in the Ukraine.

316
00:20:19.050 --> 00:20:21.621
And I don't trust Yekke
putzes let loose in Europe...

317
00:20:21.721 --> 00:20:23.873
with unlimited operational expenses.

318
00:20:23.972 --> 00:20:26.375
I was born in Israel. I'm not a Yekke.

319
00:20:26.474 --> 00:20:29.443
- Where is your grandpa from?
- Frankfurt.

320
00:20:29.644 --> 00:20:31.422
You're a Yekke.

321
00:20:31.521 --> 00:20:35.843
Your wife receives monthly
$1.000 in her bank account.

322
00:20:35.942 --> 00:20:39.555
Also. we leave messages in the
box with the operational funds.

323
00:20:39.654 --> 00:20:41.623
You can leave messages for us.

324
00:20:42.450 --> 00:20:46.461
- But there shouldn't be messages.
- I don't care about that.

325
00:20:46.787 --> 00:20:50.775
- Bring me receipts. you got me?
- I got you.

326
00:20:50.875 --> 00:20:54.969
Whatever you are doing.
somebody else is paying for it.

327
00:20:58.382 --> 00:21:00.242
We have 11 Palestinian names.

328
00:21:00.343 --> 00:21:02.369
Each had a hand in planning Munich.

329
00:21:02.470 --> 00:21:05.248
You're going to kill them.
11 men. one by one.

330
00:21:05.347 --> 00:21:06.582
They're all in Europe now.

331
00:21:06.682 --> 00:21:08.125
You'll stay there as long as it takes.

332
00:21:08.224 --> 00:21:11.295
Europe only. not the Arab countries.
That's for us. not you.

333
00:21:11.394 --> 00:21:13.548
And not Eastern Bloc.
Don't upset the Russians.

334
00:21:13.647 --> 00:21:15.365
Who needs it?

335
00:21:16.150 --> 00:21:18.701
You'll have no contact with us.

336
00:21:18.818 --> 00:21:21.263
You're not going to
give me any information?

337
00:21:21.364 --> 00:21:23.766
We deposit money from a
fund that doesn't exist...

338
00:21:23.865 --> 00:21:26.935
into a box we don't know about.
in a bank we never set foot in.

339
00:21:27.036 --> 00:21:29.564
We can't help you because we
never heard of you before.

340
00:21:29.663 --> 00:21:31.315
You'll do what the terrorists do.

341
00:21:31.414 --> 00:21:35.009
You think they report back to home base?
They don't.

342
00:21:35.336 --> 00:21:37.220
We want them dead.

343
00:21:37.755 --> 00:21:40.199
Nothing better than eating
something sweet by the sea.

344
00:21:40.298 --> 00:21:42.159
You can ask questions now.

345
00:21:42.259 --> 00:21:44.452
- Am I alone?
- Four others.

346
00:21:44.552 --> 00:21:47.373
They know useful things
like cars. documents...

347
00:21:47.472 --> 00:21:48.749
cleanup to make sure you don't...

348
00:21:48.848 --> 00:21:49.959
accidentally drop your fake passport...

349
00:21:50.058 --> 00:21:53.193
next to the dead body.
You're the team leader.

350
00:21:55.522 --> 00:21:58.425
- Who kills the targets?
- You do. Who else?

351
00:21:58.526 --> 00:22:00.970
Use guns if you have to.
but the bombs are preferable.

352
00:22:01.069 --> 00:22:03.096
One of your guys knows how to make them.

353
00:22:03.196 --> 00:22:06.474
We want everyone to read in Le Monde
some famous Arab terrorist is dead.

354
00:22:06.575 --> 00:22:08.144
Who knows who blew him up?

355
00:22:08.243 --> 00:22:10.896
- Why me?
- So what's wrong with you?

356
00:22:10.997 --> 00:22:13.881
I'm not an experienced field operative.

357
00:22:14.250 --> 00:22:17.384
- So I'm not known.
- Not even I know you now.

358
00:22:17.586 --> 00:22:19.779
And also. I lived in Frankfurt
when I was a kid...

359
00:22:19.880 --> 00:22:22.157
so I'm a Yekke Jew who knows
his way around Europe.

360
00:22:22.258 --> 00:22:25.493
That's a good reason.
Here's one more. You're ordinary.

361
00:22:25.594 --> 00:22:27.579
You aren't a sabra Charles Bronson.

362
00:22:27.680 --> 00:22:29.373
- I am a sabra.
- I know.

363
00:22:29.472 --> 00:22:31.834
I know so much about you.
You're a nice sabra...

364
00:22:31.933 --> 00:22:34.961
with a dog and a baby on the way.
You won't shoot Spanish bellhops.

365
00:22:35.061 --> 00:22:37.006
No bellhops. No civilians.

366
00:22:37.105 --> 00:22:39.424
That kind of trouble we can't afford.

367
00:22:39.525 --> 00:22:41.885
The hard thing will not be finding them.

368
00:22:41.986 --> 00:22:44.012
Some of them. anyway.
are not so carefully hidden.

369
00:22:44.113 --> 00:22:46.515
The hard thing will be not
punishing yourselves...

370
00:22:46.615 --> 00:22:48.934
by getting caught or getting killed.

371
00:22:49.035 --> 00:22:51.686
- You want the last piece of baklava?
- No.

372
00:22:51.787 --> 00:22:53.897
Smart decision. You should avoid sweets.

373
00:22:53.998 --> 00:22:57.633
After all. you just signed away
your dental insurance.

374
00:22:59.295 --> 00:23:01.739
(ON PA) This is Pierre Bouchet.
your captain. speaking.

375
00:23:01.838 --> 00:23:05.409
Welcome aboard Flight
SA 74 direct to Geneva.

376
00:23:05.509 --> 00:23:08.788
We are now at a cruising
altitude of 30.000 feet...

377
00:23:08.887 --> 00:23:11.605
and we wish you a pleasant flight.

378
00:23:17.645 --> 00:23:20.448
(TERRORIST YELLING IN ARABIC)

379
00:23:23.611 --> 00:23:25.286
(MEN YELLING IN HEBREW AND ARABIC)

380
00:23:53.098 --> 00:23:54.731
(SPEAKING ARABIC)

381
00:23:56.477 --> 00:23:59.653
Don't shoot. I don't understand
what you're saying.

382
00:24:03.400 --> 00:24:04.700
(GLASS SHATTERING)

383
00:24:12.367 --> 00:24:14.460
(YELLING IN ARABIC)

384
00:24:22.836 --> 00:24:25.054
Easy. easy. easy.

385
00:26:18.618 --> 00:26:21.127
Press the buzzer when you're done.

386
00:26:35.635 --> 00:26:36.935
(ELECTRONIC BUZZING)

387
00:26:39.431 --> 00:26:41.856
- Have a nice day.
- Thank you.

388
00:26:46.145 --> 00:26:47.756
I'm not good at it. No.

389
00:26:47.855 --> 00:26:49.215
- Hebrew?
- No.

390
00:26:49.316 --> 00:26:51.426
A team leader who cooks. What a luxury.

391
00:26:51.527 --> 00:26:53.761
- Years in the kibbutz kitchen.
- You've done this before?

392
00:26:53.862 --> 00:26:55.221
Done what?

393
00:26:55.322 --> 00:26:57.163
Sit. Come on.

394
00:26:57.907 --> 00:27:01.501
Because I joined Mossad
10 minutes ago. and I'm...

395
00:27:02.871 --> 00:27:06.298
Look. I want to kill every one
of these pigs. but...

396
00:27:07.041 --> 00:27:08.234
Thank you.

397
00:27:08.335 --> 00:27:10.988
So. some of you have
training in this kind of...

398
00:27:11.087 --> 00:27:13.156
- He sells antiques.
- Right here in Frankfurt.

399
00:27:13.257 --> 00:27:15.034
It's a front. but successful.

400
00:27:15.134 --> 00:27:17.118
I'm a documents
and identities specialist...

401
00:27:17.219 --> 00:27:20.186
with a sharp eye
for early Danish Modern.

402
00:27:20.722 --> 00:27:22.230
And you?

403
00:27:22.598 --> 00:27:24.375
Oh. I make toys.

404
00:27:24.476 --> 00:27:27.862
- I thought you made bombs.
- Toys. in Brussels.

405
00:27:28.146 --> 00:27:30.573
For bombs. I had to go to night school.

406
00:27:30.732 --> 00:27:32.509
My wife's expecting.

407
00:27:32.608 --> 00:27:34.260
- Mazel tov.
- Mazel tov.

408
00:27:34.361 --> 00:27:37.203
- Beautiful. When?
- Couple of months.

409
00:27:37.905 --> 00:27:40.290
Think we'll be done by then?

410
00:27:40.576 --> 00:27:43.376
Is it Ali Hassan Salameh we're after?

411
00:27:45.413 --> 00:27:47.923
I mean. that's the job. right?

412
00:27:48.083 --> 00:27:51.926
We're here to kill the guy who
planned Munich. Am I right?

413
00:27:54.298 --> 00:27:58.326
It's strange. isn't it. to think
of oneself as an assassin?

414
00:27:58.426 --> 00:28:00.828
Think of yourself
as something else then.

415
00:28:00.929 --> 00:28:05.691
- A soldier in a war.
- I mean. you know how to shoot...

416
00:28:06.393 --> 00:28:09.362
to assassinate people. right?

417
00:28:10.146 --> 00:28:11.839
Mazels on the baby. and all that.
That's great.

418
00:28:11.940 --> 00:28:14.575
That's just fantastic. But. I mean...

419
00:28:15.778 --> 00:28:18.412
You make dolls in a toy shop...

420
00:28:19.114 --> 00:28:22.583
and you shop for sofas...

421
00:28:22.701 --> 00:28:24.394
and you. I don't know what you do.

422
00:28:24.494 --> 00:28:27.003
Me? I worry.

423
00:28:27.580 --> 00:28:29.942
So. why'd they make you team leader?

424
00:28:30.041 --> 00:28:32.968
Because he really knows
how to cook a brisket.

425
00:28:37.090 --> 00:28:39.724
(HEARTFELT INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC)

426
00:28:59.904 --> 00:29:01.872
- Hello?
- Andreas.

427
00:29:01.990 --> 00:29:04.226
- AVNER: Surprised?
- ANDREAS: Surprised? You punched me.

428
00:29:04.326 --> 00:29:06.269
- You broke my jaw. man.
- That was 10 years ago.

429
00:29:06.369 --> 00:29:08.564
And you were sleeping
with my girlfriend.

430
00:29:08.663 --> 00:29:10.566
Listen. I'm in town. Are you around?

431
00:29:10.665 --> 00:29:12.442
Yeah. actually.
I'm here with my girlfriend.

432
00:29:12.542 --> 00:29:15.301
- Do you want to come over?
- Perfect.

433
00:29:16.046 --> 00:29:17.323
(AIN'T NO SUNSHINE
BY BILL WITHERS PLAYING)

434
00:29:17.423 --> 00:29:18.763
(SPEAKING GERMAN)

435
00:29:44.782 --> 00:29:46.352
ANDREAS: She's incredible. isn't she?

436
00:29:46.451 --> 00:29:49.461
I have no idea what she's talking about.

437
00:29:50.329 --> 00:29:51.838
(SPEAKING GERMAN)

438
00:30:23.321 --> 00:30:26.557
I miss you. man.
We really used to love each other.

439
00:30:26.657 --> 00:30:30.126
That was a long time ago.
We were in high school.

440
00:30:31.204 --> 00:30:32.546
(SPEAKING GERMAN)

441
00:30:34.540 --> 00:30:36.151
I have some names.

442
00:30:36.250 --> 00:30:40.054
Some people I need to find
for my rich American friends.

443
00:30:43.342 --> 00:30:45.518
Give me my money. Yvonne.

444
00:30:47.512 --> 00:30:50.689
- One hundred fifty.
- One hundred.

445
00:30:50.848 --> 00:30:52.084
Cash.

446
00:30:52.183 --> 00:30:54.108
$100.000.

447
00:30:57.480 --> 00:31:00.406
These people I'm looking for.
you don't know them.

448
00:31:01.108 --> 00:31:03.743
- We might.
- You don't.

449
00:31:04.946 --> 00:31:07.248
But maybe you know someone who does.

450
00:31:07.950 --> 00:31:10.667
And it's Americans you work for?

451
00:31:10.786 --> 00:31:12.920
Yes. See?

452
00:31:13.288 --> 00:31:15.088
James Madison.

453
00:31:15.790 --> 00:31:17.758
Americans.

454
00:31:17.917 --> 00:31:19.969
We'll ask some friends.

455
00:31:20.796 --> 00:31:23.030
Hiding? The Arabs are not hiding.

456
00:31:23.131 --> 00:31:25.534
- Munich was a big success for them.
- Oh?

457
00:31:25.634 --> 00:31:27.368
The implications of
Munich for the struggle...

458
00:31:27.469 --> 00:31:31.814
They got everyone's attention.
They're recruiting. making plans.

459
00:31:32.015 --> 00:31:34.023
Give me a few names.

460
00:31:37.729 --> 00:31:40.507
I can't help if I don't know
who you're trying to find.

461
00:31:40.606 --> 00:31:42.384
We'll have to trust.

462
00:31:42.483 --> 00:31:44.826
You have to cross the line.

463
00:31:45.319 --> 00:31:48.807
I trust you. You carry cash
and you don't make speeches.

464
00:31:48.906 --> 00:31:51.727
Nowadays. everyone makes speeches.
like your friend Andreas.

465
00:31:51.826 --> 00:31:53.794
Talk. talk. talk.

466
00:31:54.288 --> 00:31:56.130
Name me an Arab.

467
00:31:59.875 --> 00:32:01.509
Abu Daoud.

468
00:32:01.670 --> 00:32:03.304
Abu Youssef.

469
00:32:03.630 --> 00:32:05.306
Wael Zwaiter.

470
00:32:06.090 --> 00:32:07.807
Kamal Nasser.

471
00:32:09.510 --> 00:32:11.454
- Salameh.
- Forget Salameh. Too hard.

472
00:32:11.555 --> 00:32:14.415
Wait. Who are these guys?
Why are you trying to find Arabs?

473
00:32:14.516 --> 00:32:17.317
Sixty thousand per name. Dollars.

474
00:32:17.519 --> 00:32:21.070
- If it's good information.
- If it isn't good. it doesn't cost.

475
00:32:21.189 --> 00:32:23.740
Wael Zwaiter's here. in Rome.

476
00:32:24.192 --> 00:32:27.596
He just translated the
Arabian Nights into Italian.

477
00:32:27.695 --> 00:32:31.016
Tomorrow there's a reading. He's broke.

478
00:32:31.115 --> 00:32:33.602
He has a niece he calls
every day in Damascus.

479
00:32:33.701 --> 00:32:36.295
Are you trying to join the PLO?

480
00:32:36.579 --> 00:32:38.838
We need to talk. Alone.

481
00:32:40.541 --> 00:32:43.278
And also maybe you need
people to help with your work.

482
00:32:43.377 --> 00:32:44.654
Cars. Vans.

483
00:32:44.755 --> 00:32:46.137
(SPEAKING GERMAN)

484
00:32:57.933 --> 00:33:01.569
If you tell anybody about this.
I don't know.

485
00:33:02.480 --> 00:33:04.155
Just don't.

486
00:33:04.441 --> 00:33:06.075
Just don't.

487
00:33:23.960 --> 00:33:26.720
Anything you need. we'll provide.

488
00:33:27.130 --> 00:33:28.972
I need receipts.

489
00:33:59.704 --> 00:34:01.046
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

490
00:34:39.202 --> 00:34:40.960
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

491
00:34:45.458 --> 00:34:48.135
Keep talking. Keep talking.

492
00:35:20.284 --> 00:35:22.628
Thank you for coming. Thank you.

493
00:36:15.632 --> 00:36:17.724
(BOTH SPEAKING ITALIAN)

494
00:36:58.300 --> 00:37:00.309
(ZWAITER SPEAKING ARABIC)

495
00:37:05.264 --> 00:37:07.315
(MUSICIANS TUNING UP)

496
00:38:25.344 --> 00:38:27.396
Are you Wael Zwaiter?

497
00:38:27.764 --> 00:38:29.856
Yes. and who are you?

498
00:38:34.103 --> 00:38:36.405
Do you know why we're here?

499
00:38:39.900 --> 00:38:41.094
(ZWAITER SPEAKING ARABIC)

500
00:38:41.193 --> 00:38:43.804
- (STUTTERING) Are you Wael Zwaiter?
- He said yes already.

501
00:38:43.905 --> 00:38:45.871
He already said yes.

502
00:38:48.284 --> 00:38:50.085
What are we doing?

503
00:38:54.248 --> 00:38:56.007
What do I do?

504
00:38:56.291 --> 00:38:58.385
Do you know why we're here?

505
00:39:18.440 --> 00:39:20.007
What happened? Why didn't you shoot him?

506
00:39:20.108 --> 00:39:21.675
- We shot him.
- But I didn't hear a shot.

507
00:39:21.775 --> 00:39:23.594
We shot him eight times. maybe 10 times.

508
00:39:23.695 --> 00:39:25.347
- Did you kill him?
- He's dead.

509
00:39:25.447 --> 00:39:27.539
He shit his pants. He's dead.

510
00:39:58.771 --> 00:40:01.280
(MY GIRL BY THE TEMPTATIONS
PLAYING ON RADIO)

511
00:40:15.038 --> 00:40:17.963
Drink some wine. We're celebrating.

512
00:40:18.333 --> 00:40:21.092
That old Pesach story.

513
00:40:21.668 --> 00:40:23.195
The angels are rejoicing...

514
00:40:23.295 --> 00:40:27.099
because the Egyptians have
just drowned in the Red Sea.

515
00:40:28.342 --> 00:40:30.411
I didn't say we're rejoicing.

516
00:40:30.512 --> 00:40:32.706
I said. "We're celebrating."

517
00:40:32.806 --> 00:40:35.375
And God said to the angels.
"Why are you celebrating?

518
00:40:35.474 --> 00:40:38.003
"I've just killed a multitude
of my children."

519
00:40:38.103 --> 00:40:39.902
Mr. Zwaiter.

520
00:40:40.355 --> 00:40:45.617
He cost us. by my calculations.
roughly $352.000.

521
00:40:47.737 --> 00:40:50.056
You didn't finish the story.

522
00:40:50.155 --> 00:40:52.434
The angels respond to God.

523
00:40:52.534 --> 00:40:54.268
They say. "God. we're celebrating...

524
00:40:54.369 --> 00:40:56.938
"because when the people hear
what happened to the Egyptians...

525
00:40:57.038 --> 00:40:58.565
"they'll understand your point."

526
00:40:58.664 --> 00:41:00.297
Which was?

527
00:41:00.958 --> 00:41:03.300
Don't fuck with the Jews.

528
00:41:04.211 --> 00:41:07.157
I don't know about the rest of you.
but I'm not celebrating.

529
00:41:07.257 --> 00:41:09.432
I'm goddamn rejoicing.

530
00:41:09.717 --> 00:41:12.369
Here. Put that down.
Put it down. Get up.

531
00:41:12.469 --> 00:41:14.079
- No. please.
- Come on. dance with me.

532
00:41:14.179 --> 00:41:16.498
- Dance with me. Come on.
- No.

533
00:41:16.599 --> 00:41:18.190
Come on.

534
00:41:20.018 --> 00:41:21.777
Come on. Hey.

535
00:41:54.429 --> 00:41:57.563
This is... What shall I call you today?

536
00:41:58.224 --> 00:42:00.025
Franz Storsch.

537
00:42:01.436 --> 00:42:03.652
You can call me Louis.

538
00:42:06.481 --> 00:42:09.701
- Our service has been satisfactory?
- Pricey.

539
00:42:12.112 --> 00:42:15.182
A Jew and a Frenchman.
We could haggle forever. huh?

540
00:42:15.282 --> 00:42:19.061
- I'm not a Jew.
- What do you suppose a ramson is?

541
00:42:19.161 --> 00:42:23.340
It's a kind of a wild leek.
Not in season. but garlic will do.

542
00:42:23.875 --> 00:42:26.693
My papa sometimes loses
track of the seasons.

543
00:42:26.793 --> 00:42:29.094
I know nothing about food.

544
00:42:29.463 --> 00:42:31.764
Why does he make me shop?

545
00:42:35.135 --> 00:42:37.704
You're wondering
if I'm French Intelligence.

546
00:42:37.804 --> 00:42:39.981
Or CIA or KGB.

547
00:42:40.099 --> 00:42:43.710
Or an agent with a profitable
sideline in information.

548
00:42:43.811 --> 00:42:47.112
I could be anybody.
You could be anybody. too.

549
00:42:47.231 --> 00:42:50.074
Identity. That's the boring part now.

550
00:42:51.402 --> 00:42:53.702
Here's what isn't boring.

551
00:42:54.239 --> 00:42:56.349
As long as you don't work
for any government...

552
00:42:56.449 --> 00:42:59.226
- I'm in private business.
- Rich Americans. I heard.

553
00:42:59.327 --> 00:43:02.295
I'm in private business. too. My family.

554
00:43:02.496 --> 00:43:07.193
We can locate almost anyone
for anyone anywhere...

555
00:43:07.293 --> 00:43:09.862
and we are ideologically promiscuous.

556
00:43:09.963 --> 00:43:12.197
We love everybody. hate everybody.

557
00:43:12.297 --> 00:43:14.682
I get my feelings confused.

558
00:43:14.842 --> 00:43:17.036
If you're not working
for any government...

559
00:43:17.135 --> 00:43:18.954
we know. or we find...

560
00:43:19.054 --> 00:43:21.606
we don't find. you don't pay.

561
00:43:22.349 --> 00:43:24.668
REPORTER: (ON TV) Initially it was
the intention of the hijackers...

562
00:43:24.768 --> 00:43:28.130
to bring the Lufthansa to
Munich International Airport...

563
00:43:28.231 --> 00:43:30.425
and then take onboard
the three prisoners...

564
00:43:30.525 --> 00:43:33.760
at the end of the runway.
where Captain Klausen took his plane...

565
00:43:33.860 --> 00:43:36.389
while an Arab held a
hand grenade at his head.

566
00:43:36.489 --> 00:43:37.849
Hey. Avner.

567
00:43:37.949 --> 00:43:40.684
A Lufthansa jet was hijacked
coming from Damascus.

568
00:43:40.784 --> 00:43:43.188
The hijackers demanded
the release of three killers...

569
00:43:43.288 --> 00:43:44.438
who survived Munich...

570
00:43:44.539 --> 00:43:46.773
and the Germans said yes. instantly.

571
00:43:46.873 --> 00:43:50.068
The Arabs would be flown by
private charter plane to Zagreb.

572
00:43:50.168 --> 00:43:52.387
Look. They're free now.

573
00:43:52.547 --> 00:43:54.222
They're in Libya.

574
00:44:01.597 --> 00:44:04.523
No qualms about rejoicing
on their side. eh?

575
00:44:04.976 --> 00:44:08.945
The Israeli kills the Arabs...

576
00:44:09.731 --> 00:44:12.550
in Egypt. in Jordan.
in Lebanon. in Syria...

577
00:44:12.650 --> 00:44:14.409
Look at them.

578
00:44:15.235 --> 00:44:17.329
They're movie stars.

579
00:44:17.739 --> 00:44:21.081
But did you shoot any
of the Israeli hostages?

580
00:44:21.534 --> 00:44:26.481
It's not important to say
if I killed Israelis or not.

581
00:44:26.581 --> 00:44:28.733
We should go to Tripoli.

582
00:44:28.833 --> 00:44:30.275
Kill them.

583
00:44:30.376 --> 00:44:32.344
We don't go to Arab countries.

584
00:44:32.711 --> 00:44:35.054
We stick to the names we've been given.

585
00:44:37.425 --> 00:44:39.351
Mahmoud Hamshari.

586
00:44:45.766 --> 00:44:47.793
Do you think. looking back on it now...

587
00:44:47.893 --> 00:44:50.505
that you achieved anything
in the Munich operation?

588
00:44:50.605 --> 00:44:55.802
We have made
our voice heard by the world.

589
00:44:55.902 --> 00:44:57.869
Are those your words?

590
00:45:01.239 --> 00:45:02.516
The same thing again.

591
00:45:02.617 --> 00:45:06.688
They have made their voice heard
by the universe or the world...

592
00:45:06.788 --> 00:45:09.088
who has not been hearing before.

593
00:45:12.293 --> 00:45:14.778
Well. I believe
what he meant by this is...

594
00:45:14.878 --> 00:45:17.931
that now the world
will begin hearing us.

595
00:45:19.175 --> 00:45:23.746
We are. for 24 years.
the world's largest refugee population.

596
00:45:23.846 --> 00:45:25.914
Our homes taken from us.

597
00:45:26.014 --> 00:45:29.751
Living in camps. no future. no food.

598
00:45:29.851 --> 00:45:32.487
Nothing decent for our children.

599
00:45:32.813 --> 00:45:36.199
And. so was the attack
in Munich justified?

600
00:45:37.235 --> 00:45:39.679
The PLO condemns attacks on civilians.

601
00:45:39.778 --> 00:45:42.724
- Though for 24 years...
- Tell your newspaper that.

602
00:45:42.824 --> 00:45:46.601
...our civilians have been attacked
by the Israelis day after day...

603
00:45:46.702 --> 00:45:49.688
Tell them about all the years
and years of Palestinian blood...

604
00:45:49.789 --> 00:45:52.065
spilled by Israel.
And who mourns for us?

605
00:45:52.166 --> 00:45:54.110
You know. Israel just bombed...

606
00:45:54.210 --> 00:45:56.695
two refugee camps in Syria and Lebanon.

607
00:45:56.795 --> 00:45:59.407
- Tell them that...
- 200 people killed.

608
00:45:59.507 --> 00:46:02.744
- Right after Munich they did this.
- It did not begin in Munich.

609
00:46:02.844 --> 00:46:05.913
And where does it end?
How will it ever end?

610
00:46:06.012 --> 00:46:07.813
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

611
00:46:18.025 --> 00:46:21.179
I'm sorry. I need to use your phone.
I need to call my editor.

612
00:46:21.278 --> 00:46:23.163
Yes. yes. Sorry.

613
00:46:24.114 --> 00:46:26.641
- You see it. It's by the window.
- Thank you.

614
00:46:26.742 --> 00:46:28.710
This way. please.

615
00:46:57.398 --> 00:46:58.947
(SPEAKING A FRENCH GREETING)

616
00:47:06.740 --> 00:47:09.083
(PLAYING AN UPBEAT TUNE ON PIANO)

617
00:48:30.282 --> 00:48:33.311
This man. we don't know
what he did specifically?

618
00:48:33.411 --> 00:48:36.646
Hamshari arranged the attempted
assassination of Ben-Gurion...

619
00:48:36.746 --> 00:48:38.440
in Copenhagen a few years ago.

620
00:48:38.541 --> 00:48:40.275
Now he organizes for Fatah in France.

621
00:48:40.376 --> 00:48:41.568
- He organizes?
- Yes.

622
00:48:41.668 --> 00:48:43.487
In Tel Aviv they showed
you evidence for this?

623
00:48:43.588 --> 00:48:45.072
Not evidence. It was more...

624
00:48:45.172 --> 00:48:46.949
this is the story and I believe them.

625
00:48:47.048 --> 00:48:48.576
Why? Don't you?

626
00:48:48.675 --> 00:48:51.536
It's a crisis. a war.
You don't have to always...

627
00:48:51.637 --> 00:48:54.748
- What? Be thinking?
- Scrutinize. Yeah. think.

628
00:48:54.849 --> 00:48:57.418
You want to wire Ephraim
and ask for evidence. you do it.

629
00:48:57.518 --> 00:48:59.527
You're on your own.

630
00:49:00.021 --> 00:49:01.755
- Okay. I'm done.
- Good.

631
00:49:01.856 --> 00:49:03.989
Don't think about it.

632
00:49:05.192 --> 00:49:06.594
Okay.

633
00:49:06.693 --> 00:49:10.663
So. now. I turn it on.

634
00:49:11.865 --> 00:49:15.293
He picks up the phone.
turns on the red light...

635
00:49:16.036 --> 00:49:19.338
then I take out the key. insert it...

636
00:49:19.623 --> 00:49:21.173
and turn.

637
00:50:24.480 --> 00:50:27.407
So now we wait for the red light.

638
00:50:55.385 --> 00:50:57.329
- Is the truck blocking the signal?
- No.

639
00:50:57.429 --> 00:50:59.813
Will the remote still work?

640
00:51:16.532 --> 00:51:18.976
- Yeah. it's a powerful transmitter.
- Go back to your position.

641
00:51:19.076 --> 00:51:21.686
You can't start improvising now.
Go back to your corner.

642
00:51:21.786 --> 00:51:24.422
Don't worry. It's okay.
It's going to work.

643
00:51:46.686 --> 00:51:49.655
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

644
00:52:07.541 --> 00:52:09.007
(PHONE RINGING)

645
00:52:29.188 --> 00:52:30.655
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

646
00:52:52.418 --> 00:52:53.987
(RUNNING FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

647
00:52:54.088 --> 00:52:55.929
- Stop!
- Stop!

648
00:52:57.215 --> 00:52:58.807
Abort.

649
00:53:44.637 --> 00:53:46.606
Are we on or off?

650
00:53:50.894 --> 00:53:52.195
(PHONE RINGING)

651
00:54:03.949 --> 00:54:06.083
- Mahmoud Hamshari?
- Yes.

652
00:54:20.673 --> 00:54:23.141
He's at the hospital Cochin.

653
00:54:23.510 --> 00:54:26.079
I don't know how badly we hurt him.
They aren't saying.

654
00:54:26.179 --> 00:54:27.914
Why did you put a firecracker
in that phone?

655
00:54:28.014 --> 00:54:29.833
Because I didn't want
to blow up the building.

656
00:54:29.934 --> 00:54:32.418
- What do you want from me?
- An Arab corpse.

657
00:54:32.518 --> 00:54:35.840
Another $200.000. more or less.
to eliminate target number two.

658
00:54:35.940 --> 00:54:38.425
Yeah. if he's been eliminated.
We should stick with guns.

659
00:54:38.525 --> 00:54:40.469
No one notices a shooting.

660
00:54:40.568 --> 00:54:42.096
Bombs achieve a double objective.

661
00:54:42.195 --> 00:54:44.764
They eliminate targets
and they terrify terrorists.

662
00:54:44.864 --> 00:54:47.268
That only works when the bombs work.

663
00:54:47.367 --> 00:54:48.876
Lunch?

664
00:54:56.293 --> 00:54:59.195
REPORTER: The Israeli embassy in
London was rocked by a letter bomb...

665
00:54:59.295 --> 00:55:01.364
shortly after 9:30 this morning.

666
00:55:01.465 --> 00:55:03.867
Dr. Ami Shachori was
opening his morning mail...

667
00:55:03.967 --> 00:55:07.121
when the envelope exploded.
killing him instantly.

668
00:55:07.221 --> 00:55:11.690
They discovered seven in a mailroom
near the embassy in Earls Court.

669
00:55:12.059 --> 00:55:14.985
- I guess they missed one.
- Right after Hanukkah.

670
00:55:15.436 --> 00:55:18.822
I guess there was a big pileup
of mail and they got careless.

671
00:55:19.565 --> 00:55:21.844
They found other letters
in Israel. of course.

672
00:55:21.943 --> 00:55:25.972
Canada. Argentina. Vienna.
Kinshasa. Paris. Brussels.

673
00:55:26.072 --> 00:55:29.583
Dozens of them.
mainly posted in the Netherlands.

674
00:55:29.909 --> 00:55:31.668
It's all Black September.

675
00:55:31.911 --> 00:55:34.045
It's a response. then.

676
00:55:34.164 --> 00:55:35.648
To Hamshari.

677
00:55:35.748 --> 00:55:37.590
And to Zwaiter.

678
00:55:38.335 --> 00:55:41.094
They're talking to us.
We're in dialogue now.

679
00:55:42.255 --> 00:55:44.014
Where are you?

680
00:55:45.092 --> 00:55:47.851
I'm in New York. following a lead.

681
00:55:48.012 --> 00:55:49.894
I'll call again.

682
00:56:00.983 --> 00:56:03.159
Are you going to visit your father?

683
00:56:04.777 --> 00:56:06.931
Why is this taking so long?

684
00:56:07.030 --> 00:56:08.831
It isn't fast.

685
00:56:09.282 --> 00:56:11.876
We have the best hospitals in the world.

686
00:56:12.827 --> 00:56:16.838
When you were born. your father
was elsewhere. I was alone.

687
00:56:17.750 --> 00:56:19.675
He was in prison.

688
00:56:21.961 --> 00:56:23.971
Should you be here?

689
00:56:24.088 --> 00:56:26.097
Aren't you on duty?

690
00:56:26.425 --> 00:56:29.268
What are you going to do? Turn me in?

691
00:56:30.762 --> 00:56:32.396
How is he?

692
00:56:32.972 --> 00:56:35.125
I don't visit your father so much.

693
00:56:35.224 --> 00:56:37.753
Wilma lets him yell at her all the time.

694
00:56:37.853 --> 00:56:39.820
She depresses me.

695
00:56:45.027 --> 00:56:46.744
How are you?

696
00:56:47.780 --> 00:56:50.831
I'm managing. Don't worry about me.

697
00:56:54.911 --> 00:56:57.545
I'm proud of what you are doing.

698
00:56:57.831 --> 00:57:00.340
You don't know what I'm doing.

699
00:57:10.177 --> 00:57:14.480
I look at you and I know
everything I need to know.

700
00:57:16.849 --> 00:57:19.193
AVNER: She is frighteningly ugly.

701
00:57:19.686 --> 00:57:21.778
She takes after you.

702
00:57:22.523 --> 00:57:24.925
I want you to move. for a time.

703
00:57:25.025 --> 00:57:27.469
I've arranged a place
for us in Brooklyn.

704
00:57:27.568 --> 00:57:29.762
I can't come back to Israel.
I don't know how long for...

705
00:57:29.862 --> 00:57:30.972
New York?

706
00:57:31.072 --> 00:57:34.143
- I can see more of you this way.
- New York City?

707
00:57:34.242 --> 00:57:35.543
(KNOCKING AT DOOR)

708
00:57:36.744 --> 00:57:40.422
But I have my family here.
and your parents.

709
00:57:41.208 --> 00:57:44.027
You want my parents to help raise her?

710
00:57:44.128 --> 00:57:46.429
Look what they did to me.

711
00:57:47.338 --> 00:57:50.682
Don't you want your daughter
to be an Israeli. Avner?

712
00:57:51.885 --> 00:57:54.288
She'll always be an Israeli.

713
00:57:54.387 --> 00:57:57.291
Not in Brooklyn.
She'll just be another homeless Jew.

714
00:57:57.391 --> 00:57:59.793
I can't do what
I'm doing if I can't see you.

715
00:57:59.893 --> 00:58:01.902
What are you doing?

716
00:58:03.396 --> 00:58:06.532
Don't do it then. Avner.
This is our home.

717
00:58:06.817 --> 00:58:09.452
You're the only home I ever had.

718
00:58:10.027 --> 00:58:11.411
What?

719
00:58:12.822 --> 00:58:14.432
This is so corny.

720
00:58:14.532 --> 00:58:16.893
- It wasn't easy for me to say that.
- I bet.

721
00:58:16.994 --> 00:58:19.146
Don't laugh at me then.

722
00:58:19.246 --> 00:58:21.981
Why did I have to marry
a sentimentalist?

723
00:58:22.081 --> 00:58:24.257
You're ruining my life.

724
00:58:24.376 --> 00:58:26.677
Your mother's teasing me.

725
00:58:39.724 --> 00:58:42.400
Look at the waistline bulge on that guy.

726
00:58:42.561 --> 00:58:45.487
Look at that.
Think he might be armed. eh?

727
00:58:45.688 --> 00:58:47.739
As are the Russians.

728
00:58:48.275 --> 00:58:50.344
It's definitely him.

729
00:58:50.443 --> 00:58:52.577
Hussein Abad al-Chir.

730
00:58:52.778 --> 00:58:55.664
His room is next to Israeli newlyweds.

731
00:58:55.990 --> 00:58:58.309
They married in Cyprus
because she's not Jewish.

732
00:58:58.409 --> 00:58:59.811
A mixed marriage.

733
00:58:59.911 --> 00:59:01.355
A shande for the goyim.

734
00:59:01.454 --> 00:59:04.047
Yeah. okay.
But let's try not to blow them up.

735
00:59:04.291 --> 00:59:07.068
The KGB brings him home
every night after dark.

736
00:59:07.168 --> 00:59:09.612
He turns on the light. gets undressed...

737
00:59:09.713 --> 00:59:13.474
turns off the light.
gets into bed. we blow up the bed.

738
00:59:14.885 --> 00:59:18.371
I knew a field agent who got
too scared to sleep in his bed.

739
00:59:18.472 --> 00:59:22.023
So every night he slept
on the floor of his closet.

740
00:59:22.643 --> 00:59:24.735
He still does. every night.

741
00:59:25.228 --> 00:59:26.672
Sleeps in closets.

742
00:59:26.771 --> 00:59:29.800
Now if al-Chir sleeps in his closet.
we're in trouble.

743
00:59:29.900 --> 00:59:33.744
But if he gets in the bed.
his weight arms the device...

744
00:59:34.028 --> 00:59:36.246
it closes the circuit.

745
00:59:36.822 --> 00:59:39.541
Then we hit the remote.

746
00:59:46.708 --> 00:59:48.175
Okay.

747
00:59:48.501 --> 00:59:50.594
Okay. we're good. We're good. let's go.

748
00:59:55.384 --> 00:59:56.784
Careful.

749
00:59:56.885 --> 00:59:58.476
(KNOCKING AT DOOR)

750
01:00:00.847 --> 01:00:03.648
I've checked into the room next door.

751
01:00:05.268 --> 01:00:07.610
- Why?
- There are balconies.

752
01:00:07.853 --> 01:00:09.505
When he gets into bed...

753
01:00:09.606 --> 01:00:12.824
I give the signal by
switching off the light.

754
01:00:13.235 --> 01:00:16.452
And if the bomb's too powerful
and you're in the next room?

755
01:00:17.030 --> 01:00:18.891
Well. that won't happen.

756
01:00:18.990 --> 01:00:20.498
Right?

757
01:00:20.701 --> 01:00:22.166
Robert?

758
01:00:22.536 --> 01:00:24.460
- Robert?
- Robert?

759
01:00:25.414 --> 01:00:27.172
It won't. No.

760
01:00:27.958 --> 01:00:29.257
Okay.

761
01:00:30.668 --> 01:00:32.135
Avner.

762
01:00:34.047 --> 01:00:35.806
Boy or girl?

763
01:00:36.882 --> 01:00:38.391
A girl.

764
01:00:39.344 --> 01:00:40.936
Mazel tov.

765
01:00:44.474 --> 01:00:46.400
News from Paris.

766
01:00:47.893 --> 01:00:51.030
Dr. Hamshari succumbed to his wounds.

767
01:00:51.565 --> 01:00:55.617
So. again. mazel tov. Avner.

768
01:01:31.646 --> 01:01:34.114
(STEVE SINGING PAPA WAS A ROLLING STONE)

769
01:01:50.414 --> 01:01:52.257
Steve. shut up.

770
01:02:11.561 --> 01:02:12.902
Hey.

771
01:02:33.041 --> 01:02:34.675
Good evening.

772
01:02:35.501 --> 01:02:37.070
Good evening.

773
01:02:37.170 --> 01:02:38.655
Beautiful night.

774
01:02:38.755 --> 01:02:40.972
Beautiful night. yeah.

775
01:02:42.425 --> 01:02:45.244
- Where are you from? I can't place...
- Düsseldorf.

776
01:02:45.344 --> 01:02:48.021
Yes? I wouldn't have guessed it.

777
01:02:49.181 --> 01:02:51.525
I thought perhaps a Swede.

778
01:02:53.519 --> 01:02:56.655
I taught in Sweden.
Near Eastern languages.

779
01:02:56.856 --> 01:02:58.364
Really?

780
01:02:58.608 --> 01:03:01.635
Teaching Lebanese immigrant
women how to clean houses.

781
01:03:01.735 --> 01:03:03.429
In Swedish.

782
01:03:03.530 --> 01:03:04.996
(BOTH EXCLAIMING)

783
01:03:11.163 --> 01:03:13.422
Were you here last night?

784
01:03:13.581 --> 01:03:16.884
No. Just checked in. Just arrived.

785
01:03:18.043 --> 01:03:20.094
Don't plan to sleep.

786
01:03:20.380 --> 01:03:22.722
They keep at it all night.

787
01:03:23.007 --> 01:03:24.974
There. for hours.

788
01:03:25.844 --> 01:03:27.119
- Take a sleeping pill.
- That's okay.

789
01:03:27.219 --> 01:03:28.746
- I can sleep through anything.
- Are you sure?

790
01:03:28.847 --> 01:03:29.998
You don't want to borrow one of mine?

791
01:03:30.097 --> 01:03:31.750
- Thank you very much. It's okay.
- Really?

792
01:03:31.849 --> 01:03:32.918
Yes.

793
01:03:33.018 --> 01:03:35.152
So. good night.

794
01:03:35.686 --> 01:03:37.570
Pleasant dreams.

795
01:03:42.402 --> 01:03:45.077
(SINGING)

796
01:04:25.612 --> 01:04:27.454
Wait for the signal.

797
01:04:27.739 --> 01:04:30.039
Wait for Avner's light to go out.

798
01:05:26.630 --> 01:05:28.431
(ALARMS BLARING)

799
01:05:29.884 --> 01:05:31.643
Go! Go! Go!

800
01:05:36.016 --> 01:05:37.458
(WOMAN SCREAMING)

801
01:05:37.559 --> 01:05:39.318
(COUGHING)

802
01:05:50.697 --> 01:05:52.664
- Oh. my God!
- Help!

803
01:05:53.867 --> 01:05:56.936
WOMAN:
Oh. my eyes. My eyes. I can't see.

804
01:05:57.036 --> 01:05:58.896
Can someone help me?

805
01:05:58.996 --> 01:06:00.815
I can't see.

806
01:06:00.914 --> 01:06:02.215
Avner!

807
01:06:06.545 --> 01:06:08.512
Please! Oh. my God!

808
01:06:09.840 --> 01:06:11.516
I can't see.

809
01:06:12.969 --> 01:06:14.621
- Can you see?
- Yes.

810
01:06:14.721 --> 01:06:16.039
- The stairs are that way.
- Okay.

811
01:06:16.139 --> 01:06:18.690
- Go that way.
- Come on. Let's go!

812
01:06:20.518 --> 01:06:22.753
- It was much too powerful.
- Stop it.

813
01:06:22.853 --> 01:06:24.630
- You could've blown up innocent...
- Target number three.

814
01:06:24.731 --> 01:06:25.882
Target number three was not in doubt.

815
01:06:25.981 --> 01:06:28.300
The ceiling in the lobby cracked.
You nearly demolished...

816
01:06:28.400 --> 01:06:29.927
Avner might have been killed.

817
01:06:30.027 --> 01:06:31.512
The plastique was not what I asked for.

818
01:06:31.612 --> 01:06:33.306
It couldn't have been
the grade I specified.

819
01:06:33.405 --> 01:06:35.432
Someone changed the
marking on the explosive.

820
01:06:35.532 --> 01:06:37.434
What if someone changed the marking?

821
01:06:37.534 --> 01:06:39.521
- What do you mean?
- Louis provided the plastique.

822
01:06:39.621 --> 01:06:42.106
Avner. Louis provided the explosives?

823
01:06:42.206 --> 01:06:45.007
- Yes. Why?
- Why are we trusting him?

824
01:06:45.585 --> 01:06:47.778
We have no idea who he is.

825
01:06:47.878 --> 01:06:49.655
- He's finding our targets.
- Yes. but...

826
01:06:49.755 --> 01:06:51.949
But without him.
we'd be nowhere on this!

827
01:06:52.050 --> 01:06:55.726
The plastique was much more
powerful than what I asked for.

828
01:06:56.012 --> 01:06:58.998
Someone changed the label.
I could have killed you.

829
01:06:59.099 --> 01:07:01.376
For all we know.
Louis works for the PLO.

830
01:07:01.476 --> 01:07:03.961
They're using us to do
internal housecleaning.

831
01:07:04.061 --> 01:07:05.045
That's bullshit.

832
01:07:05.146 --> 01:07:07.780
Hey. whose fishing boat is this?

833
01:07:13.278 --> 01:07:15.288
Louis arranged it.

834
01:07:47.646 --> 01:07:49.882
There was nothing wrong
with the explosive.

835
01:07:49.983 --> 01:07:53.052
Bomb makers are nervous.
which is understandable.

836
01:07:53.152 --> 01:07:54.387
Fear makes them sloppy...

837
01:07:54.487 --> 01:07:56.163
There's nothing wrong
with my bomb maker.

838
01:07:56.322 --> 01:07:58.456
It's your explosives.

839
01:07:59.242 --> 01:08:01.960
We found three more names for you.

840
01:08:02.161 --> 01:08:04.920
- Three?
- Yes. three.

841
01:08:06.833 --> 01:08:09.467
- Thought you'd be pleased.
- I am.

842
01:08:10.586 --> 01:08:11.969
Who?

843
01:08:12.422 --> 01:08:16.557
Kemal Adwan. Kamal Nasser.
and Abu Youssef.

844
01:08:17.176 --> 01:08:19.435
Adwan and Abu Youssef.

845
01:08:19.845 --> 01:08:21.896
- Where?
- Lebanon.

846
01:08:22.431 --> 01:08:24.083
They're in Beirut.

847
01:08:24.184 --> 01:08:26.693
Adwan. Nasser. Youssef.

848
01:08:27.145 --> 01:08:29.088
Serious characters. huh?

849
01:08:29.189 --> 01:08:31.155
Extremely serious.

850
01:08:31.440 --> 01:08:35.159
Smile. Mr. Storsch.
It's a second Christmas.

851
01:08:37.070 --> 01:08:39.515
I'd like to pay you
a little extra for this.

852
01:08:39.615 --> 01:08:41.582
These three names.

853
01:08:43.243 --> 01:08:45.002
$600.000.

854
01:08:47.582 --> 01:08:49.984
Monsieur Storsch. my group...

855
01:08:50.083 --> 01:08:51.653
we don't care much for governments...

856
01:08:51.752 --> 01:08:53.195
any governments.

857
01:08:53.296 --> 01:08:55.114
We don't work with or for them.

858
01:08:55.215 --> 01:08:57.617
That's an absolute condition
of my theory.

859
01:08:57.716 --> 01:08:59.284
You understand?

860
01:08:59.385 --> 01:09:02.329
If I learn that your sudden
generosity was an attempt...

861
01:09:02.430 --> 01:09:05.792
to buy our acquiescence in
your sharing my information...

862
01:09:05.891 --> 01:09:09.587
with. let us say.
CIA or MI6 or Mossad...

863
01:09:09.686 --> 01:09:12.673
- I don't work for MI6 or CIA...
- You have no idea who you work for.

864
01:09:12.774 --> 01:09:14.282
Trust me. You don't.

865
01:09:15.193 --> 01:09:18.912
Lie to me and you will find me
abruptly unreachable...

866
01:09:19.279 --> 01:09:20.997
and unhappy.

867
01:09:21.990 --> 01:09:25.060
- Let me buy you a drink.
- No. You save your money.

868
01:09:25.161 --> 01:09:27.796
At these prices.
you're going to need it.

869
01:09:28.497 --> 01:09:30.817
EPHRAIM:
It's obviously significant information.

870
01:09:30.917 --> 01:09:35.154
Abu Youssef is like number three
in the whole Palestinian network.

871
01:09:35.255 --> 01:09:36.864
It's like Arafat. Habash. and then him.

872
01:09:36.965 --> 01:09:38.908
Of course he's significant.
Thanks for the instruction...

873
01:09:39.007 --> 01:09:40.827
- and enthusiasm.
- He's the brains of the fedayeen.

874
01:09:40.926 --> 01:09:43.162
- I know who he is.
- Next to Salameh...

875
01:09:43.262 --> 01:09:45.457
Abu Youssef is the worst
guy we're after. right?

876
01:09:45.556 --> 01:09:48.859
And Adwan. he plans all the
actions in the West Bank. right?

877
01:09:49.476 --> 01:09:51.837
We get the significance.
These are serious targets.

878
01:09:51.938 --> 01:09:53.506
- We want to go to Beirut.
- No.

879
01:09:53.605 --> 01:09:55.091
You keep away from the Arab countries.

880
01:09:55.190 --> 01:09:57.510
Mossad and the army
will take care of it.

881
01:09:57.609 --> 01:09:59.554
What is this contraption?

882
01:09:59.654 --> 01:10:02.788
You can't send the army.
We won't allow it.

883
01:10:03.824 --> 01:10:05.560
You won't allow it?

884
01:10:05.659 --> 01:10:07.729
Our source doesn't know we're Mossad.

885
01:10:07.828 --> 01:10:09.189
You aren't Mossad.

886
01:10:09.288 --> 01:10:11.983
If commandos go to Beirut.
our source will cut us off.

887
01:10:12.082 --> 01:10:15.069
Why don't you and I go for a
walk and talk about this. alone?

888
01:10:15.168 --> 01:10:16.529
The food will get cold.

889
01:10:16.628 --> 01:10:18.655
- We have to go to Beirut.
- We're good at this.

890
01:10:18.756 --> 01:10:20.533
This is our information.
this is our job.

891
01:10:20.632 --> 01:10:22.993
That's touching in a
juvenile sort of way.

892
01:10:23.094 --> 01:10:24.621
Listen. You're doing reasonably well.

893
01:10:24.720 --> 01:10:26.413
- Reasonably?
- You're spending a lot of money.

894
01:10:26.514 --> 01:10:28.273
Well. we expected that.

895
01:10:30.350 --> 01:10:33.378
Lots of people in Mossad
don't know about you.

896
01:10:33.479 --> 01:10:35.006
No one knows.

897
01:10:35.105 --> 01:10:37.675
So everyone's asking.
"Who's killing the fedayeen?

898
01:10:37.774 --> 01:10:39.761
"Is it our guys? Why weren't we told?"

899
01:10:39.860 --> 01:10:42.328
Big egos. Lots of screaming.

900
01:10:43.989 --> 01:10:46.016
I can maybe include one or two of you...

901
01:10:46.117 --> 01:10:48.560
but excluding Mossad
or the army is impossible.

902
01:10:48.661 --> 01:10:50.063
Accept it.

903
01:10:50.162 --> 01:10:52.671
We will. but our source won't.

904
01:10:53.498 --> 01:10:55.507
Who is your source?

905
01:10:56.668 --> 01:10:57.694
It's time you told me.

906
01:10:57.795 --> 01:10:59.780
That. by the way.
is not a request. It's an order.

907
01:10:59.881 --> 01:11:01.865
You can't order him.
He doesn't work for you.

908
01:11:01.966 --> 01:11:04.536
Shut up. I pay you. You work for me.

909
01:11:04.636 --> 01:11:07.831
I work for a metal box in a bank in Geneva.
The box pays me.

910
01:11:07.930 --> 01:11:10.833
- You want to find it empty?
- I want you to let us do our work!

911
01:11:10.934 --> 01:11:12.918
What's the matter with you?

912
01:11:13.019 --> 01:11:15.755
With all of you?
Grow up and do it quick.

913
01:11:15.854 --> 01:11:18.423
This is not a game. a fucking game.

914
01:11:18.524 --> 01:11:21.219
Who has the source?
Where are you getting your information?

915
01:11:21.319 --> 01:11:23.703
Give me his goddamn number!

916
01:11:24.113 --> 01:11:26.265
I hope the old lady
next door enjoyed that.

917
01:11:26.365 --> 01:11:29.876
She's a little deaf but I doubt
she had any trouble hearing you.

918
01:11:32.079 --> 01:11:35.465
Give me the source
and we'll let you take part.

919
01:11:35.625 --> 01:11:37.402
Let us go to Beirut.

920
01:11:37.502 --> 01:11:41.805
After Beirut. we'll use our source
to find the remaining targets.

921
01:11:41.922 --> 01:11:43.890
Let us do our job.

922
01:12:00.440 --> 01:12:03.827
(BAND PLAYING BLACK MAGIC WOMAN)

923
01:12:27.260 --> 01:12:30.228
A lot of manpower to shoot three guys.

924
01:12:56.122 --> 01:12:57.671
(MAN WHISTLING)

925
01:12:58.248 --> 01:13:00.466
- Ehud Barak.
- Daniel.

926
01:13:01.711 --> 01:13:04.929
(SPEAKING ARABIC)

927
01:13:37.037 --> 01:13:38.380
Go!

928
01:14:15.118 --> 01:14:17.210
Where the fuck is he?

929
01:14:19.704 --> 01:14:21.131
Door!

930
01:14:28.881 --> 01:14:30.472
- Let's go!
- Go!

931
01:14:31.175 --> 01:14:32.475
Go! Go!

932
01:14:34.386 --> 01:14:35.686
Go!

933
01:14:41.685 --> 01:14:43.528
(SPEAKING FRANTICALLY IN ARABIC)

934
01:14:45.564 --> 01:14:46.948
It's him!

935
01:15:13.926 --> 01:15:15.601
Don't shoot! No!

936
01:15:33.613 --> 01:15:35.204
Fedayeen!

937
01:15:42.162 --> 01:15:43.189
Go!

938
01:15:43.288 --> 01:15:45.297
(MACHINE GUN SHOTS)

939
01:16:26.666 --> 01:16:28.800
(FRENCH MUSIC PLAYING ON RADIO)

940
01:16:48.104 --> 01:16:51.381
- My papa would like to meet you.
- Papa?

941
01:16:51.481 --> 01:16:54.635
My papa. He runs our little group.

942
01:16:54.734 --> 01:16:56.887
I thought you ran the group.

943
01:16:56.988 --> 01:16:59.413
Everybody works for someone.

944
01:17:00.740 --> 01:17:02.792
I wasn't in Beirut.

945
01:17:02.952 --> 01:17:04.895
Well. someone was there.

946
01:17:04.996 --> 01:17:08.440
The Israeli army. according to
every newspaper on Earth.

947
01:17:08.541 --> 01:17:10.234
But you stayed away...

948
01:17:10.333 --> 01:17:13.695
after you paid so extravagantly
for the information.

949
01:17:13.796 --> 01:17:16.364
I don't like to keep my papa waiting.

950
01:17:16.465 --> 01:17:18.618
I need to tell my people
where I'm going.

951
01:17:18.717 --> 01:17:20.536
You don't know where you're going.

952
01:17:20.636 --> 01:17:23.854
And you'll need to wear this.

953
01:17:25.224 --> 01:17:26.626
Forget it. Louis. That's just crazy.

954
01:17:26.725 --> 01:17:28.650
We're done here.

955
01:17:34.817 --> 01:17:36.242
Shit.

956
01:17:36.777 --> 01:17:38.077
Wait!

957
01:17:39.238 --> 01:17:40.537
Wait!

958
01:18:26.327 --> 01:18:27.686
We're here.

959
01:18:27.787 --> 01:18:29.878
(CHILDREN SPEAKING FRENCH)

960
01:18:39.506 --> 01:18:41.265
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

961
01:18:48.306 --> 01:18:49.774
Papa!

962
01:19:05.073 --> 01:19:06.373
He's over there.

963
01:19:19.630 --> 01:19:21.740
Louis says you're a cook.

964
01:19:21.841 --> 01:19:24.141
I know how to cook. yeah.

965
01:19:24.301 --> 01:19:25.976
You help me?

966
01:19:31.141 --> 01:19:33.109
Bring these there.

967
01:19:38.023 --> 01:19:42.511
No. no. Don't wash. No. no.
They will taste like boiled sponge.

968
01:19:42.610 --> 01:19:44.555
But then why put them in the sink?

969
01:19:44.654 --> 01:19:47.099
If the juices spurt out.
it's a big mess.

970
01:19:47.198 --> 01:19:50.167
The whole kitchen will smell like piss.

971
01:19:51.744 --> 01:19:53.671
Peel off the fat.

972
01:19:56.876 --> 01:19:59.051
Let me see your hands.

973
01:20:01.713 --> 01:20:03.783
Too big for a good cook.

974
01:20:03.882 --> 01:20:06.327
That was my problem. too.
I had been a master...

975
01:20:06.426 --> 01:20:09.788
but I have thick. stupid.
butcher's hands just like yours.

976
01:20:09.889 --> 01:20:14.149
Well. we are tragic men.
Butcher's hands. gentle souls.

977
01:20:27.238 --> 01:20:29.975
These are going to be too sour to eat.

978
01:20:30.074 --> 01:20:33.711
Skin them and prick them.
boil them in sugar.

979
01:20:34.162 --> 01:20:37.715
A little torture.
and you'll see how nice they are.

980
01:20:38.417 --> 01:20:41.529
- You call me "Papa."
- I can't do that.

981
01:20:41.628 --> 01:20:44.055
- No?
- I have a papa already.

982
01:20:45.925 --> 01:20:48.100
You are devoted to him?

983
01:20:48.426 --> 01:20:50.703
Am I here because of
what happened in Beirut?

984
01:20:50.804 --> 01:20:53.605
Your papa must be proud of his son.

985
01:20:54.891 --> 01:20:58.027
We'll pick a few. Let the rest ripen.

986
01:20:58.436 --> 01:21:00.296
There are so many people to feed. but...

987
01:21:00.396 --> 01:21:02.298
But they are your family.
So you have to feed them.

988
01:21:02.399 --> 01:21:05.743
Yes. We don't work with governments.

989
01:21:05.903 --> 01:21:07.512
Louis said. But...

990
01:21:07.613 --> 01:21:11.873
But you did what you did because
you have to feed your family.

991
01:21:30.719 --> 01:21:32.537
PAPA: I blew up trains. bridges...

992
01:21:32.637 --> 01:21:35.773
and trucks full of Germans
during the war.

993
01:21:37.141 --> 01:21:42.113
My brothers were killed.
my papa and my sister were both hanged.

994
01:21:42.898 --> 01:21:44.091
She was a young girl.

995
01:21:44.190 --> 01:21:47.952
Papa. the guest doesn't want
to hear your war stories.

996
01:21:48.362 --> 01:21:52.056
We paid this price.
so Vichy scum could be replaced...

997
01:21:52.157 --> 01:21:53.975
by Gaullist scum...

998
01:21:54.076 --> 01:21:57.920
and the Nazis could be
replaced by Stalin and America.

999
01:21:58.288 --> 01:22:00.506
We stay away from governments.

1000
01:22:01.625 --> 01:22:03.384
We say grace?

1001
01:22:03.586 --> 01:22:06.136
Maybe our guest could lead us.

1002
01:22:10.259 --> 01:22:12.475
No. no. no. It's not required.

1003
01:22:14.846 --> 01:22:16.146
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

1004
01:22:20.269 --> 01:22:24.088
Our Father. who gives us obedient
and respectful clients...

1005
01:22:24.189 --> 01:22:26.990
who obey the rules according to
which our business thrives...

1006
01:22:29.653 --> 01:22:32.121
...whose prevarications
and deceptions...

1007
01:22:42.875 --> 01:22:45.842
In my despair I fathered madmen...

1008
01:22:46.502 --> 01:22:50.615
who dress like factory workers.
but never do manual labor...

1009
01:22:50.716 --> 01:22:53.743
and who read nonsense
and spout pompous bullshit...

1010
01:22:53.844 --> 01:22:57.206
about Algerians and who love nothing...

1011
01:22:57.305 --> 01:22:58.791
not Algerians or French...

1012
01:22:58.890 --> 01:23:01.859
or flesh and blood. or anything living.

1013
01:23:02.435 --> 01:23:06.465
So I have sympathy for a man
who can say. "I have a papa"...

1014
01:23:06.564 --> 01:23:08.132
and who does
what he must for his family.

1015
01:23:08.233 --> 01:23:09.699
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

1016
01:23:15.073 --> 01:23:17.041
I will say grace.

1017
01:23:25.876 --> 01:23:27.819
There's some opinion you
should be punished...

1018
01:23:27.920 --> 01:23:30.322
for what happened in Beirut.

1019
01:23:30.421 --> 01:23:32.365
We didn't know so many would die.

1020
01:23:32.466 --> 01:23:36.226
I'm in business with death.
Do you think I'm squeamish?

1021
01:23:38.471 --> 01:23:42.065
The world has been rough
with you. with your tribe.

1022
01:23:44.060 --> 01:23:47.445
It's right to respond
roughly to such treatment.

1023
01:23:48.774 --> 01:23:53.284
You pay well and you pay promptly.
so we'll continue together.

1024
01:23:54.195 --> 01:23:58.207
- But no more infractions.
- Thank you. You have my word.

1025
01:24:12.797 --> 01:24:17.100
A few andouillettes and boudins noirs...

1026
01:24:18.011 --> 01:24:22.523
black blood sausage and a
Loire cheese. Selles-sur-Cher.

1027
01:24:23.057 --> 01:24:26.444
- We cover it in ash to preserve it.
- Thank you.

1028
01:24:27.645 --> 01:24:30.072
You could have been my son.

1029
01:24:32.568 --> 01:24:35.869
But you're not. Remember that.

1030
01:24:36.988 --> 01:24:41.332
We'll do business.
but you aren't family.

1031
01:24:41.493 --> 01:24:43.293
(CAR ENGINE STARTING)

1032
01:25:29.792 --> 01:25:32.134
I have a new name for you.

1033
01:25:33.045 --> 01:25:35.386
I want Ali Hassan Salameh.

1034
01:25:37.882 --> 01:25:39.265
No.

1035
01:25:40.135 --> 01:25:42.371
You know where he is.
You know where all the names are.

1036
01:25:42.470 --> 01:25:45.439
- Salameh.
- Untouchable.

1037
01:25:47.391 --> 01:25:49.025
Salameh.

1038
01:25:56.777 --> 01:25:58.577
Zaid Muchassi.

1039
01:26:02.032 --> 01:26:05.042
Zaid Muchassi is in Athens in two weeks.

1040
01:26:05.327 --> 01:26:07.979
- Not one of our names.
- Nevertheless.

1041
01:26:08.079 --> 01:26:10.733
He is Black September's KGB contact.

1042
01:26:10.832 --> 01:26:13.193
Hussein al-Chir was the KGB contact.

1043
01:26:13.292 --> 01:26:16.654
Yes. But you put a bomb under
Monsieur al-Chir's bed in Cyprus...

1044
01:26:16.755 --> 01:26:20.265
and now he's defunct.
Muchassi is his replacement.

1045
01:26:20.425 --> 01:26:23.726
I hear he's much tougher
than his predecessor.

1046
01:26:29.350 --> 01:26:33.005
We offer Muchassi's
whereabouts at the new rate.

1047
01:26:33.104 --> 01:26:36.550
- What new rate?
- Three names for $600.000...

1048
01:26:36.649 --> 01:26:39.493
is $200.000 for one name.

1049
01:26:43.865 --> 01:26:47.144
I need you to find me a
place to work in Athens.

1050
01:26:47.243 --> 01:26:50.421
Of course. Safe house.

1051
01:27:13.020 --> 01:27:15.570
Is this Louis's idea of a joke?

1052
01:27:15.980 --> 01:27:19.073
I've had nightmares
that looked like this.

1053
01:27:20.652 --> 01:27:23.555
So when they explode. they toss
little white balls of phosphorus...

1054
01:27:23.654 --> 01:27:26.934
here all around his room.
Each ball. it's like a little sun.

1055
01:27:27.033 --> 01:27:28.976
It burns at around 5.000 degrees.

1056
01:27:29.077 --> 01:27:32.253
So the air catches fire.

1057
01:27:32.372 --> 01:27:34.733
Everything in the vicinity melts.

1058
01:27:34.832 --> 01:27:36.734
Now. the bad news is
they are grenades...

1059
01:27:36.835 --> 01:27:40.238
so I modified them to use
with a remote detonator.

1060
01:27:40.338 --> 01:27:42.282
I also should mention
that they're quite old...

1061
01:27:42.381 --> 01:27:43.681
like World War II.

1062
01:27:43.841 --> 01:27:47.228
Only four were viable.
We should dump the rest.

1063
01:27:47.970 --> 01:27:50.707
There's a porter at the hotel
where Muchassi's staying.

1064
01:27:50.806 --> 01:27:52.917
He's gonna let us in the
room when Muchassi goes out.

1065
01:27:53.018 --> 01:27:56.087
Hey. Who provided these
prehistoric explosives?

1066
01:27:56.188 --> 01:27:59.573
- Louis.
- Yeah. I'll thank him for that.

1067
01:28:05.697 --> 01:28:07.831
(DOOR OPENING IN THE STAIRWELL)

1068
01:28:13.579 --> 01:28:15.130
Tallyho.

1069
01:28:19.543 --> 01:28:21.511
(FOOTSTEPS AND VOICES APPROACHING)

1070
01:28:36.979 --> 01:28:38.881
Stop! Stop!

1071
01:28:38.980 --> 01:28:42.634
- PLO! PLO!
- ETA! ETA!

1072
01:28:42.734 --> 01:28:44.845
Put the gun down or we'll shoot.

1073
01:28:44.944 --> 01:28:48.079
Basque! Basque!

1074
01:28:50.074 --> 01:28:52.917
Okay.

1075
01:29:00.418 --> 01:29:03.595
Put the gun down! Put it down!

1076
01:29:10.636 --> 01:29:12.354
Put it down.

1077
01:29:15.975 --> 01:29:18.985
(MAN SPEAKING GERMAN)

1078
01:29:27.779 --> 01:29:29.579
(SPEAKING GERMAN)

1079
01:29:35.662 --> 01:29:40.215
- Which French? Louis?
- Who are you? English?

1080
01:29:40.917 --> 01:29:45.011
Basque. ETA. Red Army Faction.

1081
01:29:45.337 --> 01:29:49.057
He's ANC. African. African.

1082
01:29:50.301 --> 01:29:53.479
We are from Amman. I'm Ali.

1083
01:29:54.305 --> 01:29:58.442
Said. George. Abed.

1084
01:30:00.311 --> 01:30:02.488
We paid for two nights.

1085
01:30:03.606 --> 01:30:05.657
He said it was safe.

1086
01:30:05.817 --> 01:30:10.578
- He told us the same.
- Yes. Safe house.

1087
01:30:12.198 --> 01:30:13.873
Yes.

1088
01:30:16.578 --> 01:30:18.378
So we're safe?

1089
01:30:20.164 --> 01:30:21.547
Safe.

1090
01:30:22.917 --> 01:30:24.885
Everyone is safe.

1091
01:30:26.378 --> 01:30:28.971
(STATIC OVER RADIO)

1092
01:30:33.427 --> 01:30:36.145
(ARABIC INSTRUMENTAL
MUSIC PLAYING ON RADIO)

1093
01:30:50.529 --> 01:30:53.538
(FRENCH POP SONG PLAYING ON RADIO)

1094
01:31:02.289 --> 01:31:05.091
(ARABIC INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC)

1095
01:31:18.681 --> 01:31:21.524
(LET'S STAY TOGETHER BY AL GREEN)

1096
01:31:31.819 --> 01:31:35.788
Eventually the Arab states
will rise against Israel.

1097
01:31:36.158 --> 01:31:40.085
They don't like Palestinians.
but they hate the Jews more.

1098
01:31:40.494 --> 01:31:42.646
It won't be like 1967.

1099
01:31:42.747 --> 01:31:46.568
The rest of the world will see by
then what the Israelis do to us.

1100
01:31:46.667 --> 01:31:50.804
They won't help when Egypt
and Syria attack. Even Jordan.

1101
01:31:51.213 --> 01:31:53.599
Israel will cease to exist.

1102
01:31:57.095 --> 01:31:58.395
What?

1103
01:31:59.221 --> 01:32:03.567
This is a dream. You can't take back
a country you never had.

1104
01:32:03.810 --> 01:32:05.462
- You sound like a Jew.
- Fuck you.

1105
01:32:05.561 --> 01:32:08.590
I'm the voice inside your head
telling you what you already know.

1106
01:32:08.689 --> 01:32:11.240
You people have nothing to bargain with.

1107
01:32:11.525 --> 01:32:13.095
You'll never get the land back.

1108
01:32:13.194 --> 01:32:16.847
You'll all die old men in refugee
camps waiting for Palestine.

1109
01:32:16.948 --> 01:32:19.475
We have a lot of children.
They'll have children.

1110
01:32:19.576 --> 01:32:21.019
So we can wait forever.

1111
01:32:21.118 --> 01:32:24.689
And if we need to. we can make
the whole planet unsafe for Jews.

1112
01:32:24.788 --> 01:32:26.899
You kill Jews and the world
feels bad for them...

1113
01:32:27.000 --> 01:32:29.360
- and thinks you are animals.
- Yes.

1114
01:32:29.461 --> 01:32:32.530
But then the world will see how
they've made us into animals.

1115
01:32:32.631 --> 01:32:36.934
They'll start to ask questions
about the conditions in our cages.

1116
01:32:37.636 --> 01:32:41.729
You are Arabs.
There are lots of places for Arabs.

1117
01:32:43.140 --> 01:32:45.442
You're a Jew sympathizer.

1118
01:32:46.310 --> 01:32:49.445
All you Germans.
you're too soft on Israel.

1119
01:32:49.814 --> 01:32:53.217
Well. you give us money.
but you feel guilty about Hitler.

1120
01:32:53.318 --> 01:32:55.953
And the Jews exploit that guilt.

1121
01:32:56.488 --> 01:32:58.997
My father didn't gas any Jews.

1122
01:33:02.618 --> 01:33:05.796
- Tell me something. Ali.
- What?

1123
01:33:07.289 --> 01:33:10.300
Do you really miss your
father's olive trees?

1124
01:33:10.835 --> 01:33:15.264
Do you honestly think you have
to get back all that... that nothing?

1125
01:33:15.547 --> 01:33:17.283
That chalky soil and stone huts.

1126
01:33:17.384 --> 01:33:20.244
Is that what you really
want for your children?

1127
01:33:20.345 --> 01:33:22.395
It absolutely is.

1128
01:33:24.849 --> 01:33:28.025
It will take a hundred years.
but we'll win.

1129
01:33:28.979 --> 01:33:32.738
How long did it take the Jews
to get their own country?

1130
01:33:33.065 --> 01:33:36.011
How long did it take the Germans
to make Germany?

1131
01:33:36.110 --> 01:33:37.929
And look how well that worked out.

1132
01:33:38.029 --> 01:33:41.140
You don't know what it
is not to have a home.

1133
01:33:41.240 --> 01:33:44.333
That's why you European Reds
don't get it.

1134
01:33:44.661 --> 01:33:48.755
You say. "It's nothing."
but you have a home to come back to.

1135
01:33:49.416 --> 01:33:52.152
ETA. ANC. IRA...

1136
01:33:52.252 --> 01:33:55.363
we all pretend we care about
your international revolution...

1137
01:33:55.462 --> 01:33:57.430
but we don't care.

1138
01:33:58.048 --> 01:34:00.182
We want to be nations.

1139
01:34:01.386 --> 01:34:03.395
Home is everything.

1140
01:34:43.177 --> 01:34:46.896
- No. no. no.
- No. I watch.

1141
01:34:47.724 --> 01:34:50.042
You only take money
enclosed in papers. yes?

1142
01:34:50.143 --> 01:34:51.777
Of course.

1143
01:34:53.395 --> 01:34:56.614
(SPEAKING ARABIC)

1144
01:35:44.488 --> 01:35:46.122
Look there.

1145
01:35:46.698 --> 01:35:50.127
Here they come in their pumpkin coach.

1146
01:35:53.622 --> 01:35:55.923
The Russians and...

1147
01:35:58.795 --> 01:36:00.636
Cinderella.

1148
01:36:06.261 --> 01:36:08.145
(SPEAKING ARABIC)

1149
01:36:19.731 --> 01:36:23.868
Do we detonate if the other
Arabs go into the room with him?

1150
01:36:32.119 --> 01:36:34.171
Why are the Russians waiting?

1151
01:36:34.831 --> 01:36:39.091
- Why don't they leave?
- They are waiting.

1152
01:36:41.503 --> 01:36:45.599
- We are waiting. Stay calm.
- Hey. I'm calm.

1153
01:36:57.103 --> 01:37:00.029
- He's in his room. Do it.
- Is he alone?

1154
01:37:00.148 --> 01:37:04.201
- How do we know if he's alone?
- Just flip the switch. Do it.

1155
01:37:11.242 --> 01:37:12.519
- I don't understand it.
- What's wrong?

1156
01:37:12.618 --> 01:37:14.711
It's a piece of shit.

1157
01:37:15.662 --> 01:37:18.590
- What? Fuck! Not again.
- Wait. wait.

1158
01:37:18.957 --> 01:37:22.487
Where's the explosion?
It should've exploded by now.

1159
01:37:22.587 --> 01:37:24.697
- What's gone wrong?
- It's another malfunction.

1160
01:37:24.796 --> 01:37:25.823
You know what?

1161
01:37:25.923 --> 01:37:27.742
- Or maybe it's delayed...
- He has fucked up again!

1162
01:37:27.841 --> 01:37:30.161
- Or maybe it could still blow up.
- This is a waste of time!

1163
01:37:30.261 --> 01:37:32.770
Careful with that stuff. Hans.

1164
01:37:38.478 --> 01:37:40.003
- Hans!
- Hans. what are you doing?

1165
01:37:40.104 --> 01:37:42.154
Hans. get back here!

1166
01:37:44.775 --> 01:37:48.387
Hey. hey! What is he doing?

1167
01:37:48.488 --> 01:37:50.412
Hans. No. no.

1168
01:38:18.225 --> 01:38:20.777
So how long is he going to be?

1169
01:38:21.645 --> 01:38:23.213
Maybe one hour.

1170
01:38:23.314 --> 01:38:26.115
(SPEAKING GERMAN)

1171
01:38:43.751 --> 01:38:46.720
(SCREAMING IN ARABIC)

1172
01:39:07.442 --> 01:39:09.326
(HANS PANTING)

1173
01:39:13.405 --> 01:39:15.707
(SHOUTING IN GREEK)

1174
01:39:24.250 --> 01:39:25.759
I know you.

1175
01:39:27.211 --> 01:39:29.720
Stop!

1176
01:39:49.900 --> 01:39:52.118
Get in! Head down!

1177
01:40:24.435 --> 01:40:28.570
Ali? Ali? Ali?

1178
01:40:34.779 --> 01:40:37.681
Are you incapable of making
something that works?

1179
01:40:37.782 --> 01:40:39.850
Shut up! You shut up!

1180
01:40:39.951 --> 01:40:41.519
Does anybody speak Greek?

1181
01:40:41.618 --> 01:40:43.895
- Shut him up!
- Did we kill a Russian?

1182
01:40:43.996 --> 01:40:45.898
- That's not good!
- Where did you get your training?

1183
01:40:45.997 --> 01:40:48.984
Every single bomb.
every fucking one. is fucked up.

1184
01:40:49.085 --> 01:40:50.944
I was not trained to do this!

1185
01:40:51.045 --> 01:40:54.639
I was trained to dismantle bombs.
not to build them!

1186
01:40:57.092 --> 01:40:58.768
Holy shit.

1187
01:40:59.804 --> 01:41:04.082
Shin Bet wanted bomb dismantlers.
They picked me from the army.

1188
01:41:04.182 --> 01:41:05.667
- A toy maker.
- Give me some money.

1189
01:41:05.768 --> 01:41:08.610
They figured I was good
with small machines.

1190
01:41:09.188 --> 01:41:13.949
But then after Munich. they asked
if I could build bombs instead.

1191
01:41:14.819 --> 01:41:16.618
So I said yes.

1192
01:41:22.702 --> 01:41:26.171
Come on. Here.

1193
01:41:30.501 --> 01:41:33.720
(CURSING IN GREEK)

1194
01:41:34.963 --> 01:41:37.283
REPORTER: The three went to
the side of the customs hall...

1195
01:41:37.382 --> 01:41:40.411
took out pieces of their rifles.
and quickly assembled them.

1196
01:41:40.511 --> 01:41:43.664
Then they threw hand grenades into
the long queues of passengers...

1197
01:41:43.765 --> 01:41:47.752
waiting to clear passport control
and began automatic fire.

1198
01:41:47.851 --> 01:41:50.046
It was all over in a matter of minutes.

1199
01:41:50.145 --> 01:41:51.922
And the firing was indiscriminate.

1200
01:41:52.023 --> 01:41:53.739
Salameh is in London.

1201
01:41:56.485 --> 01:42:00.329
He goes there periodically to
meet with his CIA contact.

1202
01:42:00.864 --> 01:42:04.626
- His what?
- Salameh works for the CIA.

1203
01:42:05.411 --> 01:42:06.770
Bullshit.

1204
01:42:06.871 --> 01:42:09.273
Salameh guarantees
that Black September...

1205
01:42:09.372 --> 01:42:11.109
won't touch American diplomats.

1206
01:42:11.208 --> 01:42:14.153
In exchange.
the CIA gives him lots of money.

1207
01:42:14.252 --> 01:42:16.720
And they don't ask what he uses it for.

1208
01:42:18.423 --> 01:42:20.659
Did he tell them
about Munich in advance?

1209
01:42:20.760 --> 01:42:22.369
Did the CIA know about Munich?

1210
01:42:22.470 --> 01:42:24.913
The CIA didn't even know
Black September existed...

1211
01:42:25.014 --> 01:42:26.855
before Munich.

1212
01:42:27.891 --> 01:42:30.002
One of the guerrillas was
shot through the head...

1213
01:42:30.101 --> 01:42:31.295
by a ricochet bullet.

1214
01:42:31.395 --> 01:42:33.881
A second was blown up
by his own hand grenade.

1215
01:42:33.980 --> 01:42:36.365
LOUIS: Since then. he's been busy.

1216
01:42:36.943 --> 01:42:38.576
Hasn't he?

1217
01:42:39.612 --> 01:42:42.204
All manner of costly exercises.

1218
01:42:42.405 --> 01:42:44.641
Shooting tourists
in the Athens airport...

1219
01:42:44.742 --> 01:42:47.103
blowing up pharmacies in Amsterdam...

1220
01:42:47.203 --> 01:42:50.546
and that Mossad agent
in Barcelona before that.

1221
01:42:50.914 --> 01:42:55.717
Europe hasn't been this interesting
since Napoleon marched to Moscow.

1222
01:42:56.337 --> 01:42:58.762
Do you have to do that here?

1223
01:42:59.172 --> 01:43:03.225
Salameh is in London.
For the usual price.

1224
01:43:12.103 --> 01:43:14.588
We followed him from
his doctor to his hotel.

1225
01:43:14.689 --> 01:43:16.966
- He's here for eye treatment.
- Salameh. You saw him?

1226
01:43:17.065 --> 01:43:18.341
- You followed him?
- Yes.

1227
01:43:18.442 --> 01:43:20.595
- Wearing sunglasses in the rain.
- Why didn't you shoot him?

1228
01:43:20.694 --> 01:43:22.095
There were bodyguards. Civilians.

1229
01:43:22.195 --> 01:43:23.346
- Were they armed?
- Yes.

1230
01:43:23.447 --> 01:43:25.850
Well then. they're not civilians.
I'd have done it...

1231
01:43:25.949 --> 01:43:27.810
if you'd give me half a chance
to actually shoot someone.

1232
01:43:27.909 --> 01:43:30.270
I'm the only one who actually
wants to shoot these guys.

1233
01:43:30.371 --> 01:43:32.064
Maybe that's why we never let you do it.

1234
01:43:32.163 --> 01:43:34.358
- We only go after our targets.
- Since when?

1235
01:43:34.457 --> 01:43:36.152
I mean. why are
we worried about that now?

1236
01:43:36.252 --> 01:43:39.529
Do you have any idea how
many laws we've broken?

1237
01:43:39.630 --> 01:43:42.908
It's time to stop your agonizing.
It's counterproductive.

1238
01:43:43.009 --> 01:43:46.412
Including. incidentally.
the laws of the state of Israel...

1239
01:43:46.511 --> 01:43:47.788
which has no death penalty.

1240
01:43:47.889 --> 01:43:50.500
You know what your problem is. habibi?

1241
01:43:50.600 --> 01:43:52.042
You're disorientated.

1242
01:43:52.143 --> 01:43:54.545
Because the guys we're killing
are dressed in expensive suits...

1243
01:43:54.645 --> 01:43:57.006
and this is London
and not some ugly Arab village.

1244
01:43:57.105 --> 01:43:58.757
I'm not disoriented.

1245
01:43:58.858 --> 01:44:01.301
I'm keeping my sanity by
occasionally reminding myself...

1246
01:44:01.402 --> 01:44:02.470
that in spite of...

1247
01:44:02.569 --> 01:44:04.305
But it's the same
old war we're fighting...

1248
01:44:04.404 --> 01:44:05.640
I'm still. at least in principle.
a human being.

1249
01:44:05.739 --> 01:44:07.015
...over the same old scrap of desert!

1250
01:44:07.115 --> 01:44:09.476
It's just we've brought our war
to Copenhagen and Kensington...

1251
01:44:09.577 --> 01:44:12.063
and it's not like these European
anti-Semites don't deserve that.

1252
01:44:12.162 --> 01:44:15.399
Unless we learn to act like them.
we will never defeat them.

1253
01:44:15.498 --> 01:44:17.734
We act like them all the time.

1254
01:44:17.835 --> 01:44:20.070
What. you think the Palestinians
invented bloodshed?

1255
01:44:20.171 --> 01:44:22.573
How do you think we got control
of the land? By being nice?

1256
01:44:22.672 --> 01:44:25.076
Somebody pull down this man's pants.
See if he's circumcised.

1257
01:44:25.176 --> 01:44:26.661
I think we have
a double agent in our midst.

1258
01:44:26.761 --> 01:44:29.412
- Don't you dare accuse me of that!
- Stop it!

1259
01:44:29.512 --> 01:44:32.375
My son died in '67.
you foul-mouthed son of a bitch.

1260
01:44:32.475 --> 01:44:34.668
Everything you can ask.
I've done for Israel.

1261
01:44:34.769 --> 01:44:37.796
Ask for a reassignment
if this is so distasteful.

1262
01:44:37.896 --> 01:44:40.739
- Why. it's not distasteful to you?
- No.

1263
01:44:41.484 --> 01:44:44.827
'Cause the only blood that
matters to me is Jewish blood.

1264
01:44:47.073 --> 01:44:50.250
Nice job. eh. Nice job leading.

1265
01:44:52.036 --> 01:44:54.188
If the bodyguards are armed.
we kill them.

1266
01:44:54.287 --> 01:44:57.340
- They're armed.
- Well. then we kill them!

1267
01:45:02.253 --> 01:45:05.681
(SPEAKING ARABIC)

1268
01:45:43.671 --> 01:45:44.822
Taxi!

1269
01:45:44.921 --> 01:45:46.221
Taxi!

1270
01:46:29.675 --> 01:46:32.369
Roger Burke. you ugly fuck!
What are you doing in London?

1271
01:46:32.470 --> 01:46:34.454
Get your hands off me.

1272
01:46:34.555 --> 01:46:36.707
Put them up.
Put them up. you fat. wet puss!

1273
01:46:36.806 --> 01:46:38.542
Let's show these limey fucks
what we're made of.

1274
01:46:38.641 --> 01:46:41.295
Hey. wait a minute! Who the fuck...
Who do you think this is then?

1275
01:46:41.395 --> 01:46:42.671
- Roger Burke.
- Who do you think this is?

1276
01:46:42.771 --> 01:46:45.591
- No. you idiot. That is not...
- Lay off him. asshole.

1277
01:46:45.690 --> 01:46:48.658
- That's not him. Come on.
- It's Roger Burke.

1278
01:46:49.069 --> 01:46:50.220
I'm sorry about my friend. you know?

1279
01:46:50.320 --> 01:46:53.599
He's a fucked-up. belligerent guy
with a serious drinking problem.

1280
01:46:53.698 --> 01:46:57.144
- Hey. come here.
- Lose it.

1281
01:46:57.243 --> 01:46:59.521
- Come on. Calm down!
- Hey. calm down.

1282
01:46:59.622 --> 01:47:02.465
Hey. come here! Calm down!

1283
01:47:04.793 --> 01:47:08.279
Back off. Get back!

1284
01:47:08.380 --> 01:47:10.658
- Back off! Back off!
- Fuck off!

1285
01:47:10.757 --> 01:47:12.201
It's me. All right!

1286
01:47:12.301 --> 01:47:14.810
- All right. Come on.
- Fuck off!

1287
01:47:14.970 --> 01:47:17.288
- It's me. Roger. Orrin!
- Come on.

1288
01:47:17.389 --> 01:47:22.025
- It's me. Remember me? Sorry.
- It's all right.

1289
01:47:22.853 --> 01:47:25.363
You should have ducked. Roger!

1290
01:47:31.945 --> 01:47:33.514
Fucking Americans!

1291
01:47:33.613 --> 01:47:35.349
- What the fuck is that?
- Was it Salameh?

1292
01:47:35.448 --> 01:47:37.917
Yes. of course it was fucking Salameh!

1293
01:47:56.136 --> 01:47:58.104
(SOFT PIANO MUSIC PLAYING)

1294
01:47:59.430 --> 01:48:02.274
I take it she'd eat you up a bit. huh?

1295
01:48:03.351 --> 01:48:05.128
You old dog.

1296
01:48:05.229 --> 01:48:07.279
He's got some ideas.

1297
01:48:08.356 --> 01:48:11.158
- Oh. the American bloke?
- Aren't we all?

1298
01:48:11.277 --> 01:48:13.970
So you've heard these rumors?
These are wild stories.

1299
01:48:14.070 --> 01:48:16.015
- Wild stories.
- Yeah?

1300
01:48:16.114 --> 01:48:17.414
Yeah.

1301
01:48:42.140 --> 01:48:43.608
Can I?

1302
01:48:51.442 --> 01:48:56.078
I have to go to bed soon.
I work in the morning.

1303
01:48:56.779 --> 01:48:59.207
What kind of work do you do?

1304
01:49:01.577 --> 01:49:04.295
The kind that drives you to drink.

1305
01:49:04.787 --> 01:49:06.796
We must have the same job. then.

1306
01:49:08.458 --> 01:49:10.510
I love your accent.

1307
01:49:11.212 --> 01:49:13.095
I love your perfume.

1308
01:49:23.306 --> 01:49:25.774
Cuts right through the smoke.

1309
01:49:27.478 --> 01:49:28.985
Does it?

1310
01:49:29.854 --> 01:49:31.948
It's very nice.

1311
01:49:36.487 --> 01:49:39.956
Look. I don't want to be forward...

1312
01:49:40.365 --> 01:49:42.291
but it's late...

1313
01:49:42.451 --> 01:49:46.045
and I do have to get up early.

1314
01:49:46.412 --> 01:49:47.880
So...

1315
01:49:49.250 --> 01:49:51.967
- So?
- So...

1316
01:49:53.295 --> 01:49:55.805
So. you're very nice. and...

1317
01:49:59.009 --> 01:50:01.810
Are you really going to make me ask?

1318
01:50:08.394 --> 01:50:09.985
I just can't.

1319
01:50:11.020 --> 01:50:12.320
Pity.

1320
01:50:12.855 --> 01:50:15.824
- You're very attractive.
- I know.

1321
01:50:18.695 --> 01:50:20.264
If you come to your senses...

1322
01:50:20.363 --> 01:50:23.100
once you get up to your lonely room...

1323
01:50:23.199 --> 01:50:25.501
well. maybe I'll be here.

1324
01:50:26.119 --> 01:50:30.797
Or maybe I'll be in my room.
alone in bed.

1325
01:50:37.381 --> 01:50:39.055
Good night.

1326
01:50:58.359 --> 01:51:01.912
The drunk Americans.
You think they were CIA?

1327
01:51:02.405 --> 01:51:05.768
They could've been.
For all we know. Louis is CIA.

1328
01:51:05.868 --> 01:51:08.479
They work both sides. Everyone does.

1329
01:51:08.578 --> 01:51:11.523
Or Louis is Mossad.
Now. maybe he isn't...

1330
01:51:11.622 --> 01:51:13.274
but they're using him
to feed us information.

1331
01:51:13.375 --> 01:51:14.944
There's no direct link.

1332
01:51:15.043 --> 01:51:17.863
Or Mossad's giving it to CIA.
which is giving it to Louis...

1333
01:51:17.962 --> 01:51:19.782
and Ephraim's demanding
we give him Louis...

1334
01:51:19.881 --> 01:51:22.326
because he knows we expect him to do...

1335
01:51:22.426 --> 01:51:25.645
Stop chasing the mice inside your skull.

1336
01:51:30.434 --> 01:51:33.694
You know. I never thought you'd last.

1337
01:51:34.604 --> 01:51:36.547
I thought the same about you.

1338
01:51:36.648 --> 01:51:39.342
From the beginning
you seemed so reluctant.

1339
01:51:39.443 --> 01:51:41.302
I was born reluctant. Ask my mother.

1340
01:51:41.403 --> 01:51:43.012
If I can't kvetch. I can't do my job.

1341
01:51:43.113 --> 01:51:45.349
You ever feel reluctant?

1342
01:51:45.448 --> 01:51:48.000
I'm not comfortable with confusion.

1343
01:51:48.993 --> 01:51:51.689
I knew guys like you in the army.

1344
01:51:51.788 --> 01:51:54.315
You'll do any terrifying
thing you're asked to do...

1345
01:51:54.416 --> 01:51:56.926
but you have to do it running.

1346
01:51:57.752 --> 01:52:02.264
You think you can outrun
your fears. your doubts.

1347
01:52:03.841 --> 01:52:08.979
The only thing that really
scares you guys is stillness.

1348
01:52:10.640 --> 01:52:13.859
But everyone's overtaken. eventually.

1349
01:52:15.311 --> 01:52:17.881
Now. the mice need a brandy.
Will you join me?

1350
01:52:17.980 --> 01:52:20.551
No. I'm going to go upstairs.
straight to bed.

1351
01:52:20.650 --> 01:52:21.885
You okay drinking by yourself?

1352
01:52:21.984 --> 01:52:24.953
It's just a shot to numb the brain.
Good night.

1353
01:52:28.408 --> 01:52:29.708
Oh.

1354
01:52:29.909 --> 01:52:33.128
- Beware of the local honey trap.
- Indeed?

1355
01:52:33.747 --> 01:52:36.798
You can't miss her. You don't want to.

1356
01:52:48.679 --> 01:52:50.311
(PHONE RINGING)

1357
01:52:57.186 --> 01:52:58.380
Hello.

1358
01:52:58.479 --> 01:53:00.631
This is a trunk call from Mr. Storsch.

1359
01:53:00.731 --> 01:53:01.966
Do you accept the charges?

1360
01:53:02.067 --> 01:53:05.220
Shit. Avner. you woke up the baby.
but that's okay... I mean...

1361
01:53:05.319 --> 01:53:06.996
How are you?

1362
01:53:07.864 --> 01:53:09.289
I miss you.

1363
01:53:09.824 --> 01:53:12.935
You're in England or Australia...

1364
01:53:13.036 --> 01:53:15.712
- or the North Pole...
- Yeah. that's right.

1365
01:53:17.498 --> 01:53:19.609
So listen. I was thinking...

1366
01:53:19.710 --> 01:53:22.529
when I'm finished doing
what I'm doing here...

1367
01:53:22.628 --> 01:53:24.280
I want to come to Brooklyn to see you.

1368
01:53:24.381 --> 01:53:27.117
Brooklyn is depressing.
It's got more churches than Jerusalem.

1369
01:53:27.216 --> 01:53:28.368
Listen to her talk.

1370
01:53:28.469 --> 01:53:30.060
(BABY GURGLING)

1371
01:53:31.054 --> 01:53:34.439
- Can you hear me? Can she hear me?
- Yeah. yeah.

1372
01:53:35.100 --> 01:53:38.610
Hey. Talk to me.

1373
01:53:40.939 --> 01:53:43.698
Daphna. make her talk.

1374
01:53:45.777 --> 01:53:47.161
(BABY GURGLING)

1375
01:53:53.911 --> 01:53:55.211
Dada.

1376
01:53:59.832 --> 01:54:03.219
(WHISPERING)
Hey. Hey. sweetheart. It's your papa.

1377
01:54:05.087 --> 01:54:07.389
This is my voice. darling.

1378
01:54:09.426 --> 01:54:12.728
This is what I sound like.
Don't forget. okay?

1379
01:54:14.640 --> 01:54:17.501
Listen. I have to get her to bed.
She's tired.

1380
01:54:17.600 --> 01:54:19.819
She'll dream about you.

1381
01:54:52.051 --> 01:54:56.188
REPORTER: We're standing at a distance.
as instructed by the terrorists.

1382
01:54:57.099 --> 01:54:59.585
Are we going? Is it to the airport?

1383
01:54:59.685 --> 01:55:00.918
Can we talk to someone. just to say...

1384
01:55:01.019 --> 01:55:02.962
Shut up. okay?
Just get on the bus. okay?

1385
01:55:03.063 --> 01:55:06.675
Just to tell our families.
Just to say we are all right!

1386
01:55:06.774 --> 01:55:09.511
Everybody. just relax. okay?
Relax! Calm down.

1387
01:55:09.610 --> 01:55:13.681
We will ride this bus and fly away.
After. you go back to your home...

1388
01:55:13.782 --> 01:55:16.082
or to your Olympic Games.

1389
01:55:26.461 --> 01:55:28.136
(REPORTERS CHATTERING)

1390
01:55:31.841 --> 01:55:34.475
(POLICE DOGS BARKING)

1391
01:56:01.787 --> 01:56:03.087
(GROANING)

1392
01:56:05.792 --> 01:56:07.509
(EXCLAIMING)

1393
01:56:07.627 --> 01:56:09.677
(SHOUTING)

1394
01:56:19.180 --> 01:56:21.940
(SPEAKING HEBREW)

1395
01:56:23.060 --> 01:56:25.485
(SPEAKING ARABIC)

1396
01:56:30.567 --> 01:56:31.867
(GASPING)

1397
01:56:59.011 --> 01:57:00.311
(SNIFFING)

1398
01:57:13.819 --> 01:57:16.953
Carl. You asshole.

1399
01:57:17.447 --> 01:57:19.414
I saw her first.

1400
01:57:37.466 --> 01:57:38.934
Carl?

1401
01:58:40.488 --> 01:58:42.663
(SCREAMING)

1402
01:59:16.106 --> 01:59:19.784
She's Dutch. not political.
entirely business-minded.

1403
01:59:20.028 --> 01:59:22.871
She lives in Hoorn. She's there now.

1404
01:59:23.155 --> 01:59:25.141
This is dependable information.

1405
01:59:25.242 --> 01:59:27.476
For which you pay nothing.

1406
01:59:27.577 --> 01:59:30.188
We're giving you this.
You understand why?

1407
01:59:30.287 --> 01:59:32.524
Because you want me to believe
that you had nothing to do...

1408
01:59:32.623 --> 01:59:34.484
with the murder of my partner.

1409
01:59:34.583 --> 01:59:38.363
We inhabit a world of
intersecting secrecies.

1410
01:59:38.462 --> 01:59:41.992
We live and die at the places
where those secrecies meet.

1411
01:59:42.091 --> 01:59:44.268
That's what we accept.

1412
01:59:44.845 --> 01:59:48.063
We buy information for you
from your enemies.

1413
01:59:49.265 --> 01:59:50.375
This alerts them.

1414
01:59:50.475 --> 01:59:53.068
You're not the only people
looking for names.

1415
01:59:53.770 --> 01:59:55.756
You're telling me I'm being hunted now?

1416
01:59:55.855 --> 01:59:58.716
He's telling you it's time
for you to quit.

1417
01:59:58.817 --> 02:00:02.636
The race is not to the swift.
nor the battle to the strong...

1418
02:00:02.737 --> 02:00:05.747
but time and chance happens to them all.

1419
02:00:18.127 --> 02:00:20.179
Evil falls suddenly.

1420
02:00:22.172 --> 02:00:24.515
Who can say when it falls?

1421
02:00:31.474 --> 02:00:33.942
(ANNOUNCEMENTS OVER PA IN FRENCH)

1422
02:00:47.615 --> 02:00:50.250
So you're really gonna kill her?

1423
02:00:51.286 --> 02:00:55.631
- All this blood comes back to us.
- Eventually it will work.

1424
02:00:55.789 --> 02:00:58.800
Even if it takes years. we'll beat them.

1425
02:00:59.502 --> 02:01:01.470
We're Jews. Avner.

1426
02:01:01.755 --> 02:01:03.823
Jews don't do wrong because
our enemies do wrong.

1427
02:01:03.923 --> 02:01:06.408
We can't afford to be
that decent anymore.

1428
02:01:06.509 --> 02:01:08.953
I don't know that we ever
were that decent.

1429
02:01:09.054 --> 02:01:13.123
Suffering thousands of years of
hatred doesn't make you decent.

1430
02:01:13.224 --> 02:01:16.920
But we're supposed to be righteous.
That's a beautiful thing.

1431
02:01:17.020 --> 02:01:18.337
That's Jewish.

1432
02:01:18.438 --> 02:01:20.905
That's what I knew.
that's what I was taught.

1433
02:01:21.815 --> 02:01:24.594
And now I'm losing it.
and I lose that. that's...

1434
02:01:24.694 --> 02:01:27.119
- That's...
- That's everything.

1435
02:01:27.488 --> 02:01:29.331
That's my soul.

1436
02:01:31.993 --> 02:01:35.462
You need to go rest somewhere.
You don't have to do this one.

1437
02:01:37.373 --> 02:01:39.548
When I need you again. I'll find you.

1438
02:01:52.805 --> 02:01:54.523
(TRAIN WHISTLE BLARING)

1439
02:02:21.710 --> 02:02:24.219
(RADIO PLAYING)

1440
02:02:32.720 --> 02:02:35.188
Excuse me. Who are you?

1441
02:02:43.189 --> 02:02:44.989
Do you know why we're here?

1442
02:02:45.399 --> 02:02:47.199
I want to get dressed. okay?

1443
02:02:53.365 --> 02:02:56.877
Maybe you want to hire me.
You know how good I am.

1444
02:03:01.875 --> 02:03:03.300
No. Don't.

1445
02:03:03.835 --> 02:03:06.677
It's such a fucking waste of talent.

1446
02:03:17.974 --> 02:03:19.792
Where're you going? Stay here.

1447
02:03:19.893 --> 02:03:21.650
Shell. Shell.

1448
02:03:22.270 --> 02:03:23.653
Yeah.

1449
02:03:40.997 --> 02:03:42.296
(GASPING)

1450
02:03:59.306 --> 02:04:00.856
Leave it.

1451
02:04:18.868 --> 02:04:22.337
HANS: In seven months we've
killed six of the 11 names.

1452
02:04:22.831 --> 02:04:25.274
We've killed one replacement.

1453
02:04:25.375 --> 02:04:27.444
One of our targets
is in prison and four...

1454
02:04:27.543 --> 02:04:30.679
including Ali Hassan Salameh.
are at large.

1455
02:04:31.296 --> 02:04:33.640
One of our own has fallen.

1456
02:04:34.134 --> 02:04:37.119
Since we began. the other side has
sent letter bombs to 11 embassies...

1457
02:04:37.220 --> 02:04:39.520
hijacked three planes...

1458
02:04:39.721 --> 02:04:43.649
killed 130 passengers in Athens
and wounded scores more...

1459
02:04:43.976 --> 02:04:46.628
and killed our military
attaché in Washington.

1460
02:04:46.729 --> 02:04:50.132
Some of it was done by a Venezuelan
called Carlos the Jackal...

1461
02:04:50.233 --> 02:04:52.135
who replaced Zaid Muchassi...

1462
02:04:52.234 --> 02:04:54.703
who replaced Hussein al-Chir.

1463
02:04:55.572 --> 02:04:59.416
Black September's original
leadership has been decimated.

1464
02:05:01.202 --> 02:05:03.645
But new leaders are emerging...

1465
02:05:03.746 --> 02:05:06.672
for whom Black September
wasn't violent enough.

1466
02:05:09.377 --> 02:05:11.945
And to dispatch our six
dispatched targets...

1467
02:05:12.046 --> 02:05:15.324
we must have spent something
close to $2 million. right?

1468
02:05:15.425 --> 02:05:19.060
You've been cooking.
Are you expecting company?

1469
02:05:19.636 --> 02:05:22.271
Mrs. Meir says to the Knesset...

1470
02:05:23.765 --> 02:05:26.502
the world must see that killing Jews...

1471
02:05:26.603 --> 02:05:29.863
will be from now on an
expensive proposition.

1472
02:05:31.774 --> 02:05:34.408
But killing Palestinians
isn't exactly cheap.

1473
02:05:37.738 --> 02:05:41.625
- If all 11 were dead. you'd stop?
- Yes.

1474
02:05:42.618 --> 02:05:47.005
You're lying.
What about their replacements?

1475
02:05:47.457 --> 02:05:50.591
With each time we kill.
we create six more.

1476
02:05:51.211 --> 02:05:52.987
Maybe they'll have to
keep killing them. then.

1477
02:05:53.087 --> 02:05:54.595
Forever.

1478
02:05:55.506 --> 02:05:57.574
Five targets are still alive.

1479
02:05:57.675 --> 02:05:59.661
That's five men that need to be killed.

1480
02:05:59.761 --> 02:06:02.287
Eventually you forget that in
the beginning you hated doing it.

1481
02:06:02.387 --> 02:06:03.957
For me personally.
I feel less every day.

1482
02:06:04.056 --> 02:06:06.042
One day I'm going to wake up.
I'm going to kill...

1483
02:06:06.141 --> 02:06:09.444
I'm going to go back to bed.
I'm not going to feel anything at all.

1484
02:06:11.230 --> 02:06:15.551
Hey. Hans? You know there's a rule
in the book against blind drunks.

1485
02:06:15.652 --> 02:06:17.554
Why don't you stop drinking
and eat something?

1486
02:06:17.654 --> 02:06:21.247
I mean. there's enough food
here to feed Bangladesh.

1487
02:06:23.952 --> 02:06:27.921
I keep seeing that Dutch woman.
you know. sprawled out like that.

1488
02:06:31.083 --> 02:06:34.194
It's not that I wish
we hadn't killed her.

1489
02:06:34.295 --> 02:06:37.389
I wish I had let you
close up her housecoat.

1490
02:06:37.673 --> 02:06:41.518
Yeah. but you weren't yourself.

1491
02:06:56.149 --> 02:06:57.617
(WHISPERING) Avner.

1492
02:07:00.195 --> 02:07:01.496
Avner.

1493
02:07:03.783 --> 02:07:05.082
Avner.

1494
02:07:05.368 --> 02:07:08.670
I went to Hans' flat above
the antique shop...

1495
02:07:08.912 --> 02:07:12.172
just to check up on him
because he was so...

1496
02:07:12.875 --> 02:07:15.694
Anyway. he's gone somewhere.
and I waited all night...

1497
02:07:15.795 --> 02:07:17.720
and he's not come back.

1498
02:07:38.568 --> 02:07:40.034
Knife.

1499
02:07:44.823 --> 02:07:47.167
They didn't take anything.

1500
02:12:00.871 --> 02:12:02.462
(PHONE RINGING)

1501
02:12:09.005 --> 02:12:10.345
What?

1502
02:12:40.994 --> 02:12:43.087
It will be beautiful.

1503
02:12:44.247 --> 02:12:48.009
LOUIS: Ali Hassan Salameh is
in Tarifa on the Spanish coast.

1504
02:12:48.793 --> 02:12:52.698
He's at a compound guarded
by all the predictable trouble.

1505
02:12:52.797 --> 02:12:55.850
Bomb makers often die accidental deaths.

1506
02:12:57.927 --> 02:13:00.520
In Athens you shot a KGB agent.

1507
02:13:02.350 --> 02:13:05.944
Many people must want to kill you.
Monsieur Storsch.

1508
02:13:06.061 --> 02:13:09.655
But why would I do that?
You pay better than anyone.

1509
02:13:14.904 --> 02:13:17.704
It's dangerous going after Salameh.

1510
02:13:18.698 --> 02:13:20.875
But he planned the Munich massacre.

1511
02:13:24.704 --> 02:13:28.716
Eliminate him. and they'll let you
go home. Don't you think?

1512
02:13:31.921 --> 02:13:33.887
Yes. Louis. I do.

1513
02:13:37.592 --> 02:13:40.728
You could have a kitchen
like that someday.

1514
02:13:43.556 --> 02:13:47.652
It costs dearly. but home always does.

1515
02:14:26.891 --> 02:14:29.027
(FESTIVE VOICES)

1516
02:14:44.033 --> 02:14:46.836
Shit! It's like a funhouse in there.

1517
02:14:47.328 --> 02:14:49.505
Can you tell how many?

1518
02:15:09.018 --> 02:15:10.693
That's him.

1519
02:15:14.899 --> 02:15:17.408
Are you sure it's him. Avner?

1520
02:15:18.778 --> 02:15:20.828
You have to be sure.

1521
02:15:31.791 --> 02:15:33.091
(YELLING IN ARABIC)

1522
02:16:22.757 --> 02:16:24.409
- I'm Avner Kaufman.
- We know.

1523
02:16:24.510 --> 02:16:27.203
- You want to ride with us?
- Hop in.

1524
02:16:27.304 --> 02:16:28.895
Please.

1525
02:16:34.435 --> 02:16:37.780
I'm Amos. This is Avi. Shin Bet.

1526
02:16:38.398 --> 02:16:40.324
We're not supposed
to know who you are...

1527
02:16:41.192 --> 02:16:42.386
because we're not officers.

1528
02:16:42.486 --> 02:16:45.538
We're just shit
and no one tells us shit.

1529
02:16:47.031 --> 02:16:49.959
We've heard about what you've done.

1530
02:16:51.662 --> 02:16:54.212
We want to say it's an honor
to meet you.

1531
02:16:59.128 --> 02:17:01.512
It's an honor for me. too.

1532
02:17:10.638 --> 02:17:12.958
I have no problems with
anything you guys did...

1533
02:17:13.058 --> 02:17:16.193
except the woman
on the houseboat in Hoorn.

1534
02:17:16.520 --> 02:17:18.213
Steve's told us about her.

1535
02:17:18.314 --> 02:17:19.506
We took a leave of absence...

1536
02:17:19.606 --> 02:17:20.882
and killed her off the company clock.

1537
02:17:20.983 --> 02:17:22.050
Don't be an idiot.

1538
02:17:22.150 --> 02:17:25.494
Otherwise. as I said. we have no
problems with the job you did.

1539
02:17:26.155 --> 02:17:28.224
Except three of my men died.

1540
02:17:28.324 --> 02:17:29.390
According to your colleague...

1541
02:17:29.490 --> 02:17:31.602
I should say. emphatically.
according to your colleague...

1542
02:17:31.701 --> 02:17:33.228
not in any way your fault.

1543
02:17:33.328 --> 02:17:34.479
He sings your praises.

1544
02:17:34.579 --> 02:17:37.465
Best guy he ever worked for. and so on.

1545
02:17:41.045 --> 02:17:44.406
He says this French group...
Louis was his name?

1546
02:17:44.505 --> 02:17:47.493
They sold the terrorists information
regarding your whereabouts.

1547
02:17:47.593 --> 02:17:49.602
They helped kill your men.

1548
02:17:50.595 --> 02:17:52.832
I know Steve believes that.
but it's not true.

1549
02:17:52.932 --> 02:17:54.522
Tell us who they are.

1550
02:17:56.852 --> 02:17:59.153
They won't work with you.

1551
02:18:00.272 --> 02:18:03.424
- It's about loyalty.
- You're an Israeli officer.

1552
02:18:03.524 --> 02:18:06.409
That's your only loyalty! That's it!

1553
02:18:09.156 --> 02:18:10.539
Okay.

1554
02:18:11.700 --> 02:18:14.727
This is General Hofi of
the Northern Command.

1555
02:18:14.827 --> 02:18:16.629
You look good.

1556
02:18:17.039 --> 02:18:20.609
Listen. the Prime Minister is
proud of you and your men.

1557
02:18:20.709 --> 02:18:22.736
She wishes she could tell you herself.
but she can't.

1558
02:18:22.835 --> 02:18:25.054
She never heard of you. right?

1559
02:18:25.547 --> 02:18:28.993
Good. She says you've done
a great thing for your people.

1560
02:18:29.093 --> 02:18:30.768
For Israel.

1561
02:18:34.889 --> 02:18:38.024
That's it.
There is no medal or anything.

1562
02:18:49.405 --> 02:18:52.747
June 16. 1973. Avner Kaufman interview.

1563
02:18:54.909 --> 02:18:56.502
Go ahead.

1564
02:19:00.582 --> 02:19:02.882
Tell me what you learned.

1565
02:19:05.546 --> 02:19:07.573
- What I learned?
- Yes.

1566
02:19:07.673 --> 02:19:09.724
What did you learn?

1567
02:19:12.051 --> 02:19:13.537
For God's sake!

1568
02:19:13.637 --> 02:19:16.314
Tell me the names and
numbers of your sources.

1569
02:19:20.394 --> 02:19:21.836
Avner. tell me.

1570
02:19:21.936 --> 02:19:25.238
Tell me the names and
numbers of your sources.

1571
02:19:26.358 --> 02:19:27.867
Please.

1572
02:19:28.818 --> 02:19:32.038
I can have you court-martialed.
and I might.

1573
02:19:32.448 --> 02:19:35.915
You can't. I don't work for you.

1574
02:19:37.536 --> 02:19:39.336
I don't exist.

1575
02:19:41.372 --> 02:19:44.592
- You look terrible.
- I'm not good right now.

1576
02:19:46.836 --> 02:19:50.972
You don't need to tell me anything.
It's taken a lot from you.

1577
02:19:51.382 --> 02:19:55.727
- I'm alive. right?
- And the rest sorts itself out.

1578
02:19:56.930 --> 02:20:00.648
I'm not a fool. Avner.
I never said you were a fool.

1579
02:20:10.443 --> 02:20:14.538
Everyone in Europe died.
Most of my family.

1580
02:20:15.199 --> 02:20:16.683
A huge family.

1581
02:20:16.783 --> 02:20:18.416
(MAKING BLOWING SOUND)

1582
02:20:20.328 --> 02:20:22.772
I never talked to you about it.

1583
02:20:22.872 --> 02:20:26.132
- I knew.
- You knew? So what was there to say?

1584
02:20:27.293 --> 02:20:29.905
I didn't die. because I came here.

1585
02:20:30.004 --> 02:20:33.408
When I arrived. I walked up to
the top of a hill in Jerusalem...

1586
02:20:33.509 --> 02:20:36.620
and prayed for a child.

1587
02:20:36.719 --> 02:20:39.707
I never prayed before.
but I was praying then.

1588
02:20:39.807 --> 02:20:43.359
And I could feel every one
of them praying with me.

1589
02:20:46.604 --> 02:20:48.988
You are what we prayed for.

1590
02:20:49.858 --> 02:20:52.325
What you did. you did for us.

1591
02:20:52.486 --> 02:20:55.596
You did for your daughter.
but also for us.

1592
02:20:55.697 --> 02:20:59.208
Every one of the ones who died.
died wanting this.

1593
02:21:00.536 --> 02:21:04.230
We had to take it.
because no one will ever give it to us.

1594
02:21:04.331 --> 02:21:07.842
A place to be a Jew among Jews.
subject to no one.

1595
02:21:09.710 --> 02:21:12.430
I thank God for hearing my prayer.

1596
02:21:14.299 --> 02:21:16.641
Do you want to know. Mama?

1597
02:21:17.886 --> 02:21:20.728
Do you want me to tell you what I did?

1598
02:21:22.432 --> 02:21:23.773
No.

1599
02:21:24.934 --> 02:21:28.695
Whatever it took. whatever it takes.

1600
02:21:30.273 --> 02:21:35.536
A place on Earth.
We have a place on Earth.

1601
02:21:36.697 --> 02:21:38.246
At last.

1602
02:21:47.833 --> 02:21:50.217
- What's this?
- Baklava.

1603
02:21:50.793 --> 02:21:53.988
From Rehovot? The only edible
baklava is from the Arabs in Jaffa.

1604
02:21:54.088 --> 02:21:56.282
Eat it on the plane. You're too thin.

1605
02:21:56.382 --> 02:21:58.726
I hope it gives you a bellyache.

1606
02:21:59.844 --> 02:22:01.163
Listen. forget it.

1607
02:22:01.263 --> 02:22:03.957
You go see your wife. your child.
rest for a few more months.

1608
02:22:04.057 --> 02:22:05.751
Then we're gonna
put you back in the field.

1609
02:22:05.851 --> 02:22:07.585
Not Europe. Probably Latin America.

1610
02:22:07.685 --> 02:22:11.197
You think it over. Rest. Avner.
Then you come back.

1611
02:22:13.149 --> 02:22:14.492
No.

1612
02:22:21.532 --> 02:22:23.459
(CHURCH BELLS TOLLING)

1613
02:22:41.136 --> 02:22:42.203
That's all right.

1614
02:22:42.304 --> 02:22:45.748
Oh. no. no. no. It's okay. It's okay.

1615
02:22:45.849 --> 02:22:49.317
Look at that beautiful hair.

1616
02:23:36.023 --> 02:23:37.657
Nightmares?

1617
02:23:38.527 --> 02:23:39.868
Yes.

1618
02:23:43.031 --> 02:23:44.915
Come back to bed.

1619
02:23:47.201 --> 02:23:49.836
I have no idea where I should be.

1620
02:23:55.918 --> 02:24:00.681
The place is nice.
You've made it really nice.

1621
02:24:01.717 --> 02:24:03.851
The kitchen's too big.

1622
02:25:21.546 --> 02:25:24.472
Sylvie. I need to speak to your father.

1623
02:25:26.300 --> 02:25:28.102
Is Louis there?

1624
02:25:29.470 --> 02:25:32.207
I need to speak to your father.
Have him call me.

1625
02:25:32.307 --> 02:25:36.402
212-664-7665.

1626
02:25:36.811 --> 02:25:39.570
I'll wait. He must call me. I'll wait.

1627
02:25:40.272 --> 02:25:41.989
(PHONE RINGING)

1628
02:25:43.485 --> 02:25:45.326
Am I being hunted?

1629
02:25:45.694 --> 02:25:47.306
Is my family being hunted?

1630
02:25:47.406 --> 02:25:52.394
How is your father? He's well?
Your family is well?

1631
02:25:52.494 --> 02:25:56.064
I don't know. How is my family?
Are they well?

1632
02:25:56.164 --> 02:25:57.481
Are they going to be okay?

1633
02:25:57.582 --> 02:26:00.318
I'm sending you a parcel
of sausage and cheese.

1634
02:26:00.418 --> 02:26:03.572
Real cheese.
The kind you can't find in America.

1635
02:26:03.672 --> 02:26:07.474
It isn't pasteurized.
so it won't taste like shit.

1636
02:26:08.510 --> 02:26:11.811
It's a real pleasure to
hear your voice again.

1637
02:26:12.638 --> 02:26:15.190
I think about you with concern.

1638
02:26:15.350 --> 02:26:17.275
Do you believe me?

1639
02:26:19.020 --> 02:26:20.319
Avner?

1640
02:26:20.855 --> 02:26:23.031
You believe me. Avner?

1641
02:26:24.942 --> 02:26:26.594
You know my name?

1642
02:26:26.694 --> 02:26:28.495
Of course I do.

1643
02:26:29.864 --> 02:26:32.123
Now. listen to me. It's important.

1644
02:26:33.200 --> 02:26:36.378
No harm will come to you from me.

1645
02:26:39.207 --> 02:26:40.506
(PHONE CLICKING)

1646
02:26:40.791 --> 02:26:42.300
(DIAL TONE)

1647
02:27:01.061 --> 02:27:04.906
You can't go in there. sir.
It's a restricted area. Sir?

1648
02:27:05.316 --> 02:27:07.426
I tried to stop him.
I don't know who this guy is.

1649
02:27:07.527 --> 02:27:10.370
Security!

1650
02:27:11.406 --> 02:27:13.015
If you're Mossad. you know who I am.

1651
02:27:13.115 --> 02:27:15.977
If you don't.
tell Ephraim Avner came to see him.

1652
02:27:16.076 --> 02:27:17.478
Being in this room
is by appointment only.

1653
02:27:17.578 --> 02:27:19.064
Shut up and listen to me.

1654
02:27:19.164 --> 02:27:21.649
I won't hesitate to kill
other people's children...

1655
02:27:21.750 --> 02:27:23.777
- if you hurt my child. Understand?
- Do I know you. sir?

1656
02:27:23.877 --> 02:27:26.947
Or wives if you hurt my wife.
or fathers if you hurt my father.

1657
02:27:27.047 --> 02:27:29.240
I don't care. I'll go to the newspapers.

1658
02:27:29.341 --> 02:27:32.201
I'll give every name of everybody
who was in the meetings.

1659
02:27:32.301 --> 02:27:36.313
I'll tell them everything if you
don't leave my family alone! Okay?

1660
02:31:26.661 --> 02:31:28.210
(SCREAMING)

1661
02:32:05.032 --> 02:32:06.708
I love you.

1662
02:32:31.266 --> 02:32:32.734
Avner.

1663
02:32:38.023 --> 02:32:39.825
Phone for you.

1664
02:32:40.067 --> 02:32:41.826
He's Israeli.

1665
02:32:46.449 --> 02:32:49.084
You think we'd hurt your family?

1666
02:32:49.244 --> 02:32:52.129
I think anyone is capable of anything.

1667
02:32:52.246 --> 02:32:54.880
I think you're losing your mind.

1668
02:32:59.546 --> 02:33:01.595
Did I commit murder?

1669
02:33:04.509 --> 02:33:06.577
I want you to give me proof
that everyone we killed...

1670
02:33:06.677 --> 02:33:07.703
had a hand in Munich.

1671
02:33:07.804 --> 02:33:10.122
I don't discuss such things
with people who don't exist.

1672
02:33:10.222 --> 02:33:12.709
You want to discuss.
come back to existence.

1673
02:33:12.808 --> 02:33:14.835
You want your daughter
to grow up in exile?

1674
02:33:14.935 --> 02:33:16.819
I want evidence.

1675
02:33:20.233 --> 02:33:23.844
Professor Hamshari with
the beautiful wife and child?

1676
02:33:23.944 --> 02:33:27.182
He was implicated in a failed
assassination attempt on Ben-Gurion.

1677
02:33:27.281 --> 02:33:29.601
He was recruiting for Fatah France.

1678
02:33:29.700 --> 02:33:30.977
You stopped him.

1679
02:33:31.076 --> 02:33:32.561
We should have tried
to bring him to Israel.

1680
02:33:32.662 --> 02:33:34.689
And Zwaiter.
your harmless little writer in Rome?

1681
02:33:34.789 --> 02:33:38.066
He was behind the bomb on
El Al flight 76 in 1968.

1682
02:33:38.166 --> 02:33:39.943
He was working on
another bomb last August.

1683
02:33:40.043 --> 02:33:41.111
I could go on and on with this.

1684
02:33:41.211 --> 02:33:43.739
According to evidence nobody has seen.

1685
02:33:43.840 --> 02:33:46.658
If these people committed crimes.
we should have arrested them.

1686
02:33:46.759 --> 02:33:48.559
Like Eichmann.

1687
02:33:48.761 --> 02:33:50.579
If these guys live. Israelis die.

1688
02:33:50.680 --> 02:33:54.941
Whatever doubts you have.
Avner. you know this is true.

1689
02:34:04.277 --> 02:34:06.513
You did well. but you're unhappy.

1690
02:34:06.612 --> 02:34:09.289
- I killed seven men.
- Not Salameh.

1691
02:34:09.824 --> 02:34:11.583
We'll get him. of course.

1692
02:34:14.537 --> 02:34:16.796
You think you were the only team?

1693
02:34:17.165 --> 02:34:20.150
It's a big operation.
You were only a part.

1694
02:34:20.251 --> 02:34:22.343
Does that assuage your guilt?

1695
02:34:23.296 --> 02:34:25.471
Did we accomplish anything at all?

1696
02:34:25.590 --> 02:34:28.325
Every man we killed has
been replaced by worse.

1697
02:34:28.425 --> 02:34:31.412
Why cut my fingernails?
They'll grow back.

1698
02:34:31.512 --> 02:34:33.915
Did we kill to replace
the terrorist leadership...

1699
02:34:34.014 --> 02:34:35.375
or the Palestinian leadership?

1700
02:34:35.475 --> 02:34:37.126
You tell me what we've done.

1701
02:34:37.226 --> 02:34:38.920
You killed them for the
sake of a country...

1702
02:34:39.020 --> 02:34:40.569
you now choose to abandon.

1703
02:34:41.772 --> 02:34:45.635
The country your mother and father built.
that you were born into.

1704
02:34:45.735 --> 02:34:48.745
You killed them for Munich.
for the future. for peace.

1705
02:34:50.281 --> 02:34:53.393
There's no peace at the end of this.
no matter what you believe.

1706
02:34:53.493 --> 02:34:56.771
- You know this is true.
- Here's what I know.

1707
02:34:56.870 --> 02:34:58.856
Your father is sick.
your mother will be alone.

1708
02:34:58.957 --> 02:35:02.467
You're a sabra.
Your wife and daughter are sabras.

1709
02:35:03.085 --> 02:35:05.594
What I came to say is this...

1710
02:35:06.505 --> 02:35:08.138
come home.

1711
02:35:22.146 --> 02:35:24.406
Come to my house for dinner tonight.

1712
02:35:25.941 --> 02:35:27.968
Come on.
You're a Jew. you're a stranger.

1713
02:35:28.068 --> 02:35:30.638
It's written someplace or
other that I'm meant to...

1714
02:35:30.737 --> 02:35:33.747
ask you to come and break bread with me.

1715
02:35:34.032 --> 02:35:38.878
So break bread with me. Ephraim.

1716
02:35:42.583 --> 02:35:43.924
No.
